('gombo_seche_dried_okra_powder_gabonese', 'Gombo Séché (Dried Okra Powder)', 296, 17.0, 49.0, 3.5, 18.5, 4.0, 10, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['gombo séché (dried okra powder)', 'powder', 'sliced dried'], 'traditional', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Dried and powdered okra is used as a thickening agent and flavor enhancer in soups and stews throughout Gabon. It is a preserved form allowing okra flavor year-round.', TRUE),
('poivre_de_selim_grains_of_selim_uda_gabonese', 'Poivre de Selim (Grains of Selim / Uda)', 300, 5.0, 60.0, 8.0, 20.0, 0.5, 2, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['poivre de selim (grains of selim / uda)', 'whole', 'ground'], 'traditional', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Grains of Selim are a distinctly smoky, peppery West and Central African spice used to season soups and grilled meats in Gabon. They impart a unique earthiness that defines local cuisine.', TRUE),
('noisettes_de_palme_palm_kernel_nuts_gabonese', 'Noisettes de Palme (Palm Kernel Nuts)', 534, 7.5, 22.0, 49.5, 9.0, 1.5, 30, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['noisettes de palme (palm kernel nuts)', 'raw', 'roasted'], 'traditional', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Palm kernel nuts cracked and eaten as a snack or used to produce palm kernel oil are a traditional food throughout Gabon. Children enjoy cracking them open with stones.', TRUE),
('plantain_roti_au_four_oven_roasted_plantain_gabonese', 'Plantain Rôti au Four (Oven-Roasted Plantain)', 130, 1.3, 31.0, 0.5, 2.3, 10.0, 200, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['plantain rôti au four (oven-roasted plantain)', 'ripe', 'slightly unripe', 'with butter'], 'traditional', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Whole ripe plantains roasted in an oven or on a grill until caramelized are a popular side dish in Gabonese homes. The heat concentrates the natural sugars for an intensely sweet result.', TRUE),
('haricots_blancs_cuisines_cooked_white_beans_gabonese', 'Haricots Blancs Cuisinés (Cooked White Beans)', 122, 7.5, 22.0, 0.5, 6.3, 0.5, 200, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['haricots blancs cuisinés (cooked white beans)', 'with tomato', 'with onion', 'plain'], 'fusion', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'White beans cooked with onions, tomatoes, and spices are a hearty side dish in urban Gabonese cooking. They are eaten with rice or bread as an affordable protein-rich meal.', TRUE),
('pois_chiches_chickpeas_gabonese', 'Pois Chiches (Chickpeas)', 164, 8.9, 27.0, 2.6, 7.6, 4.8, 200, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['pois chiches (chickpeas)', 'in stew', 'in salad', 'roasted'], 'fusion', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Chickpeas have been introduced to Gabonese urban cuisine through Lebanese and North African diaspora communities. They are served in stews, salads, and as a snack when roasted.', TRUE),
('salade_dharicots_blancs_gabonese', 'Salade d''Haricots Blancs', 120, 7.0, 21.5, 1.5, 6.0, 1.5, 150, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['salade d''haricots blancs', 'with lemon', 'with vinaigrette', 'with onion'], 'fusion', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Cold white bean salad dressed with lemon, parsley, and olive oil is a French-inspired side dish found in Libreville bistros and modern Gabonese home cooking.', TRUE),
('radis_en_salade_radish_salad_gabonese', 'Radis en Salade (Radish Salad)', 16, 0.7, 3.4, 0.1, 1.6, 1.9, 100, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['radis en salade (radish salad)', 'with butter', 'with vinaigrette', 'plain'], 'fusion', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Sliced fresh radishes with butter and sea salt is a classic French amuse-bouche and appetizer served in French-influenced Gabonese dining. Radishes are grown in highland garden plots.', TRUE),
('salade_olivier_olivier_salad_gabonese', 'Salade Olivier (Olivier Salad)', 185, 5.5, 14.0, 13.0, 2.0, 3.5, 200, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['salade olivier (olivier salad)', 'with chicken', 'with tuna', 'vegetarian'], 'fusion', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'A hearty salad with potatoes, carrots, peas, eggs, and mayonnaise is popular at Gabonese celebrations and parties. Its origins reflect the international culinary culture of Libreville.', TRUE),
('chips_de_banane_plantain_plantain_chips_gabonese', 'Chips de Banane Plantain (Plantain Chips)', 509, 2.3, 64.5, 26.5, 4.5, 3.5, 50, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['chips de banane plantain (plantain chips)', 'salted', 'unsalted', 'spicy'], 'traditional', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Thin sliced plantain deep-fried into crispy chips are a popular snack sold in bags throughout Gabon. They are eaten at all times of day and are produced both industrially and artisanally.', TRUE),
('chips_de_manioc_cassava_chips_gabonese', 'Chips de Manioc (Cassava Chips)', 498, 2.0, 65.0, 25.5, 2.5, 1.0, 50, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['chips de manioc (cassava chips)', 'salted', 'seasoned', 'plain'], 'traditional', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Thinly sliced cassava deep-fried into crispy chips are a widely sold snack in Gabonese markets and roadside stands. They are crunchy, salty, and a popular alternative to imported potato chips.', TRUE),
('salade_de_gesiers_gizzard_salad_gabonese', 'Salade de Gésiers (Gizzard Salad)', 175, 17.5, 5.0, 9.5, 1.0, 2.0, 150, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['salade de gésiers (gizzard salad)', 'warm', 'cold', 'with mustard dressing'], 'fusion', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Warm chicken gizzard salad with lettuce, onions, and vinaigrette is a French bistro-style dish found in Gabonese restaurants. The tender gizzards are confit or pan-fried before serving.', TRUE),
('mousse_davocat_avocado_mousse_gabonese', 'Mousse d''Avocat (Avocado Mousse)', 155, 1.8, 8.5, 13.5, 5.0, 0.8, 120, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['mousse d''avocat (avocado mousse)', 'with lime', 'with tomato', 'spiced'], 'fusion', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Pureed avocado seasoned with lime, salt, and pepper serves as a modern spread and side dish in Gabonese upscale restaurants. It reflects the growing influence of contemporary French cuisine.', TRUE),
