('cacahuetes_au_piment_spicy_peanuts_gabonese', 'Cacahuetes au Piment (Spicy Peanuts)', 581, 25.6, 17.8, 49.1, 8.3, 2.1, 30, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['cacahuetes au piment (spicy peanuts)', 'arachides pimentees', 'pistaches pili-pili'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Peanuts roasted with dried pili-pili chili flakes and salt; a beloved Gabonese snack sold at sporting events and bars. The heat level varies by vendor and region.', TRUE),
('noix_de_cajou_grillees_roasted_cashews_gabonese', 'Noix de Cajou Grillees (Roasted Cashews)', 574, 15.3, 30.2, 46.4, 3.3, 5.9, 30, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['noix de cajou grillees (roasted cashews)', 'noix de cajou salee', 'anacarde grille'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Dry-roasted cashews sold as a premium snack at Libreville supermarkets and hotel bars. Cashew cultivation exists in southern Gabon and cashews feature in modern Gabonese snack culture.', TRUE),
('chips_de_plantain_plantain_crisps_gabonese', 'Chips de Plantain (Plantain Crisps)', 500, 3.6, 60.7, 25.0, 3.6, 3.8, 40, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['chips de plantain (plantain crisps)', 'chips plantain', 'crisps de banane plantain'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Thinly sliced green plantain deep-fried in palm oil until crisp; sold in plastic bags at kiosks and petrol stations across Gabon. Green plantains give a savory starchy crunch distinct from sweet banana chips.', TRUE),
('biscuits_coco_coconut_biscuits_gabonese', 'Biscuits Coco (Coconut Biscuits)', 463, 5.8, 62.1, 21.4, 3.2, 28.6, 50, 15, 'research', ARRAY['biscuits coco (coconut biscuits)', 'sables coco', 'biscuits a la noix de coco'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Crispy baked biscuits made with desiccated coconut and sugar; produced by small bakeries in Libreville and sold at corner shops. Coconut biscuits reflect French colonial pastry traditions adapted to local ingredients.', TRUE),
('gateau_sec_au_gingembre_ginger_shortbread_gabonese', 'Gateau Sec au Gingembre (Ginger Shortbread)', 441, 5.2, 63.8, 18.1, 0.9, 24.3, 50, 20, 'research', ARRAY['gateau sec au gingembre (ginger shortbread)', 'sable gingembre', 'cookie gingembre'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Dry shortbread cookies flavored with fresh grated ginger; a popular tea-time snack in Gabonese households and sold at artisanal bakeries. Ginger is widely grown in Gabon and used extensively in cuisine.', TRUE),
('gateau_de_manioc_sucre_sweet_cassava_cake_gabonese', 'Gateau de Manioc Sucre (Sweet Cassava Cake)', 228, 2.1, 48.6, 3.8, 1.4, 22.1, 100, 80, 'research', ARRAY['gateau de manioc sucre (sweet cassava cake)', 'cake manioc', 'gateau yuca'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Dense steamed or baked cake made from grated cassava, coconut milk, and palm sugar; a traditional Gabonese dessert served at family celebrations and sold at weekend markets. The texture is moist and slightly chewy.', TRUE),
('gateau_banane_banana_cake_gabonese', 'Gateau Banane (Banana Cake)', 264, 4.1, 46.2, 7.8, 1.6, 24.8, 100, 80, 'research', ARRAY['gateau banane (banana cake)', 'cake a la banane', 'pain de banane sucre'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Moist cake made with overripe bananas, flour, eggs, and butter; popular at Gabonese birthday parties and Sunday family gatherings. The abundance of ripe plantains and bananas makes this a practical and beloved dessert.', TRUE),
('gateau_ananas_pineapple_upside_down_cake_gabonese', 'Gateau Ananas (Pineapple Upside-Down Cake)', 271, 3.8, 47.3, 8.2, 0.9, 29.6, 100, 90, 'research', ARRAY['gateau ananas (pineapple upside-down cake)', 'tarte renversee ananas', 'gateau renverse ananas'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Caramelized pineapple cake made with fresh Gabonese pineapples known for their exceptional sweetness; served at restaurants and special occasions in Libreville. Gabon produces some of the finest pineapples in Central Africa.', TRUE),
('tarte_aux_fruits_tropicaux_tropical_fruit_tart_gabonese', 'Tarte aux Fruits Tropicaux (Tropical Fruit Tart)', 248, 4.2, 36.8, 9.7, 1.8, 18.4, 120, 120, 'research', ARRAY['tarte aux fruits tropicaux (tropical fruit tart)', 'tarte tropicale', 'tarte aux fruits'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Pastry shell filled with custard cream and topped with seasonal tropical fruits including mango, papaya, and pineapple; a French-influenced dessert found in Libreville patisseries and upscale restaurants.', TRUE),
('creme_caramel_a_la_noix_de_coco_coconut_creme_caramel_gabonese', 'Creme Caramel a la Noix de Coco (Coconut Creme Caramel)', 158, 4.8, 23.6, 5.1, 0.0, 22.1, 120, 120, 'research', ARRAY['creme caramel a la noix de coco (coconut creme caramel)', 'flan coco', 'creme renversee coco'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Classic French creme caramel adapted with coconut milk instead of dairy cream; a popular dessert in Gabonese restaurants and hotels. The coconut version is lighter and reflects local ingredient availability.', TRUE),
('mousse_au_chocolat_gabonaise_gabonese_chocolate_mousse_gabonese', 'Mousse au Chocolat Gabonaise (Gabonese Chocolate Mousse)', 312, 6.8, 26.4, 20.1, 2.4, 21.8, 100, 100, 'research', ARRAY['mousse au chocolat gabonaise (gabonese chocolate mousse)', 'mousse chocolat', 'mousseux au cacao'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Light chocolate mousse made with dark chocolate imported from neighboring Cameroon and Sao Tome; a dessert found in Libreville fine dining restaurants. Gabon sits at the heart of Central Africa''s cacao belt.', TRUE),
('glace_a_la_mangue_mango_ice_cream_gabonese', 'Glace a la Mangue (Mango Ice Cream)', 142, 2.8, 22.6, 4.9, 0.8, 19.8, 100, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['glace a la mangue (mango ice cream)', 'creme glacee mangue', 'sorbet mangue'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Homemade or artisanal ice cream made with fresh Gabonese mangoes; sold by mobile ice cream vendors in Libreville and at beach kiosks. Mangoes ripen in abundance during the dry season.', TRUE),
('sorbet_corossol_soursop_sorbet_gabonese', 'Sorbet Corossol (Soursop Sorbet)', 98, 0.8, 24.8, 0.2, 1.6, 21.4, 150, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['sorbet corossol (soursop sorbet)', 'glace corossol', 'granita corossol'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Refreshing frozen sorbet made from the pulp of soursop (corossol) fruit which grows wild in Gabonese forests; sold at juice bars and beachside kiosks. The intensely floral flavor makes it a uniquely Central African treat.', TRUE),
('glace_a_la_papaye_papaya_ice_cream_gabonese', 'Glace a la Papaye (Papaya Ice Cream)', 138, 2.4, 21.8, 4.6, 0.6, 18.9, 100, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['glace a la papaye (papaya ice cream)', 'creme glacee papaye', 'sorbet papaye'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Creamy ice cream made with fresh papaya puree; a popular dessert at Gabonese restaurants and sold at seaside stalls in Port-Gentil. Papaya trees are ubiquitous in Gabon and fruit year-round.', TRUE),
('bonbons_de_coco_coconut_candy_gabonese', 'Bonbons de Coco (Coconut Candy)', 407, 2.8, 58.6, 18.9, 3.8, 48.2, 30, 15, 'research', ARRAY['bonbons de coco (coconut candy)', 'sucre coco', 'candy coco', 'noix de coco confite'], 'candy', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Traditional coconut sweets made by simmering shredded coconut with sugar and natural coloring; sold in colorful paper wrappers at market stalls. A childhood favorite in Gabon, often made pink, yellow, or white.', TRUE),
('caramels_a_la_banane_banana_caramels_gabonese', 'Caramels a la Banane (Banana Caramels)', 381, 2.1, 68.4, 10.2, 0.6, 54.8, 30, 8, 'research', ARRAY['caramels a la banane (banana caramels)', 'caramel banane', 'toffee banane'], 'candy', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Soft caramel candies flavored with mashed banana; made by artisan confectioners in Libreville and sold at markets and street kiosks. The tropical flavor profile distinguishes them from standard French caramels.', TRUE),
('sucettes_a_la_mangue_mango_lollipops_gabonese', 'Sucettes a la Mangue (Mango Lollipops)', 364, 0.0, 91.0, 0.0, 0.0, 78.4, 20, 12, 'research', ARRAY['sucettes a la mangue (mango lollipops)', 'lollipop mangue', 'sucette tropicale'], 'candy', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Hard sugar candy lollipops flavored with mango concentrate; sold at school tuck shops and market stalls across Gabon. A favorite treat among Gabonese schoolchildren that uses the country''s most abundant tropical fruit flavor.', TRUE),
('bonbons_au_tamarin_tamarind_candy_gabonese', 'Bonbons au Tamarin (Tamarind Candy)', 272, 2.8, 71.5, 0.6, 3.1, 58.9, 30, 10, 'research', ARRAY['bonbons au tamarin (tamarind candy)', 'billes de tamarin', 'tamarin sucre'], 'candy', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Sweet and sour tamarind balls rolled in sugar; sold throughout Central and West African markets including Gabon''s street stalls. The sweet-sour-spicy combination of tamarind with chili and sugar is addictively popular.', TRUE),
('nougat_a_la_noix_cashew_nougat_gabonese', 'Nougat a la Noix (Cashew Nougat)', 436, 6.8, 64.2, 17.4, 1.2, 52.6, 40, 20, 'research', ARRAY['nougat a la noix (cashew nougat)', 'nougat cajou', 'torrone cajou'], 'candy', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Chewy nougat candy studded with roasted cashews; made by artisan confectioners in Libreville using both local cashews and imported ingredients. A premium sweet sold at specialty food shops and holiday markets.', TRUE),
('praline_darachide_peanut_praline_gabonese', 'Praline d''Arachide (Peanut Praline)', 521, 14.8, 52.4, 29.6, 3.8, 42.1, 40, 20, 'research', ARRAY['praline d''arachide (peanut praline)', 'croquant arachide', 'brittle cacahuete'], 'candy', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Caramelized sugar coated peanut clusters similar to brittle; a popular homemade confection sold at Gabonese markets and church fundraisers. Peanut pralines are given as gifts during family celebrations.', TRUE),
('halva_de_sesame_sesame_halva_gabonese', 'Halva de Sesame (Sesame Halva)', 516, 12.6, 52.8, 28.4, 4.2, 38.6, 40, 40, 'research', ARRAY['halva de sesame (sesame halva)', 'halawa sesame', 'confiserie sesame'], 'candy', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Dense sesame paste confection sweetened with honey or sugar syrup; introduced through North African and Lebanese merchant communities established in Libreville. Found at Lebanese-owned food shops and specialty markets.', TRUE),
('caramel_au_lait_de_coco_coconut_milk_caramel_gabonese', 'Caramel au Lait de Coco (Coconut Milk Caramel)', 396, 1.6, 62.8, 15.4, 0.4, 58.6, 30, 10, 'research', ARRAY['caramel au lait de coco (coconut milk caramel)', 'caramel coco', 'toffee lait coco'], 'candy', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Soft milk caramels made with coconut milk instead of dairy milk giving a tropical richness; produced by small confectionery workshops in Libreville. Often wrapped in banana leaf for traditional presentation.', TRUE),
('barre_de_coco_et_chocolat_coconut_chocolate_bar_gabonese', 'Barre de Coco et Chocolat (Coconut Chocolate Bar)', 486, 4.8, 52.6, 28.4, 4.1, 42.8, 50, 50, 'research', ARRAY['barre de coco et chocolat (coconut chocolate bar)', 'barre bounty artisanale', 'chocolate coco bar'], 'candy', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Coconut filling dipped in dark chocolate; a Gabonese take on the Bounty bar produced by local confectioners using coconut from coastal areas. Sold at supermarkets and specialty shops in Libreville.', TRUE),
('pain_depices_gabonais_gabonese_spiced_bread_cake_gabonese', 'Pain d''Epices Gabonais (Gabonese Spiced Bread Cake)', 348, 5.8, 68.4, 6.2, 1.8, 38.4, 80, 60, 'research', ARRAY['pain d''epices gabonais (gabonese spiced bread cake)', 'cake epices et miel', 'gateau de miel epice'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Honey and spice loaf cake made with ginger, cinnamon, and forest honey from Gabonese forests; a French colonial legacy adapted with local honey and spices. Served at Christmas and Easter celebrations.', TRUE),
('crepe_sucree_au_coco_sweet_coconut_crepe_gabonese', 'Crepe Sucree au Coco (Sweet Coconut Crepe)', 231, 6.4, 32.8, 8.6, 1.2, 12.4, 120, 80, 'research', ARRAY['crepe sucree au coco (sweet coconut crepe)', 'crepe coco sucree', 'crepe tropicale'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Thin French-style crepes filled with shredded coconut and sugar; sold from mobile crepe stands that operate in Libreville evenings and at cultural festivals. Reflects Gabon''s strong French culinary heritage.', TRUE),
('crepe_a_la_banane_et_miel_banana_honey_crepe_gabonese', 'Crepe a la Banane et Miel (Banana Honey Crepe)', 219, 5.8, 36.4, 6.4, 1.4, 16.8, 120, 80, 'research', ARRAY['crepe a la banane et miel (banana honey crepe)', 'crepe banane miel', 'crepe dessert banane'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Crepes filled with sliced banana and drizzled with wild forest honey; a popular dessert crepe sold at Libreville''s evening food stalls. Forest honey from Gabon''s forests is prized for its rich floral flavor.', TRUE),
('gauffre_tropicale_tropical_waffle_gabonese', 'Gauffre Tropicale (Tropical Waffle)', 292, 6.8, 44.2, 10.4, 1.1, 14.8, 120, 120, 'research', ARRAY['gauffre tropicale (tropical waffle)', 'gaufre aux fruits tropicaux', 'waffle gabonais'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Belgian-style waffles topped with fresh tropical fruit and condensed milk; sold at modern street food stalls in Libreville''s Quartier Louis area. Reflects the urban cosmopolitan food culture of the Gabonese capital.', TRUE),
('beignets_de_coco_coconut_doughnuts_gabonese', 'Beignets de Coco (Coconut Doughnuts)', 362, 5.4, 48.6, 16.8, 2.4, 14.2, 80, 30, 'research', ARRAY['beignets de coco (coconut doughnuts)', 'beignets noix de coco', 'doughnuts coco'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Fried dough balls made with fresh coconut milk and shredded coconut; a coastal Gabonese specialty sold near the beaches of Libreville and Cap Lopez. The coconut gives a rich tropical flavor to the classic beignet.', TRUE),
('beignets_de_mais_corn_fritters_gabonese', 'Beignets de Mais (Corn Fritters)', 242, 5.6, 36.8, 8.4, 2.8, 4.2, 100, 40, 'research', ARRAY['beignets de mais (corn fritters)', 'galettes de mais frites', 'akara de mais'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Savory-sweet fritters made from ground corn mixed with onion and spices, deep-fried until golden; sold at morning markets throughout Gabon. Often eaten for breakfast alongside sweet tea.', TRUE),
('akara_gabonais_black_eyed_pea_fritters_gabonese', 'Akara Gabonais (Black-Eyed Pea Fritters)', 241, 9.8, 28.4, 10.6, 4.8, 1.8, 100, 35, 'research', ARRAY['akara gabonais (black-eyed pea fritters)', 'beignets haricots', 'koose', 'awara'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Deep-fried fritters made from ground black-eyed peas seasoned with onion and pili-pili; a West African-influenced street food popular among Gabonese communities with Beninese or Togolese heritage. Sold at morning markets.', TRUE),
('boulettes_de_plantain_frites_fried_plantain_balls_gabonese', 'Boulettes de Plantain Frites (Fried Plantain Balls)', 196, 1.6, 38.4, 4.8, 2.2, 10.4, 120, 30, 'research', ARRAY['boulettes de plantain frites (fried plantain balls)', 'boules plantain', 'croquettes de plantain'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Mashed ripe plantain formed into balls and deep-fried; a sweet starchy snack sold at market stalls throughout Gabon. Sometimes filled with peanut paste for added richness and protein.', TRUE),
('baton_de_manioc_grille_grilled_cassava_stick_gabonese', 'Baton de Manioc Grille (Grilled Cassava Stick)', 174, 1.6, 41.2, 0.4, 1.9, 1.4, 150, 150, 'research', ARRAY['baton de manioc grille (grilled cassava stick)', 'chikwangue grillee', 'manioc en baton grille'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Fermented and compressed cassava paste formed into cylinders and grilled over charcoal; sold wrapped in banana leaves at roadside stalls. This is one of the most fundamental street foods of the Gabonese Bantu peoples.', TRUE),
('papaye_verte_pimentee_spiced_green_papaya_gabonese', 'Papaye Verte Pimentee (Spiced Green Papaya)', 43, 0.9, 9.8, 0.2, 1.8, 4.6, 150, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['papaye verte pimentee (spiced green papaya)', 'salade papaye verte', 'papaye au citron piment'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Shredded or sliced unripe papaya seasoned with lemon juice, chili, and salt; sold by street vendors as a refreshing snack in Libreville''s heat. Reflects Southeast Asian and broader tropical influence on Gabonese food culture.', TRUE),
('mangue_verte_au_piment_green_mango_with_chili_gabonese', 'Mangue Verte au Piment (Green Mango with Chili)', 60, 0.8, 15.2, 0.4, 1.6, 12.8, 150, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['mangue verte au piment (green mango with chili)', 'mango verte pimentee', 'mangue au sel et piment'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Sliced green mango dusted with salt, chili powder, and sometimes lime; a popular street snack sold in small plastic bags at markets. Children and adults alike eat this tart-spicy combination as an afternoon treat.', TRUE),
('noix_datanga_grillee_grilled_bush_butter_nuts_gabonese', 'Noix d''Atanga Grillee (Grilled Bush Butter Nuts)', 412, 6.8, 14.2, 38.4, 5.8, 2.4, 80, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['noix d''atanga grillee (grilled bush butter nuts)', 'safou grille', 'bush butter grille', 'prune d''afrique grillee'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'The fruit of the African pear tree (Dacryodes edulis) roasted over charcoal until tender; sold at roadside stalls throughout Gabon. The rich buttery flesh is eaten directly or spread on baton de manioc as a nutritious street snack.', TRUE),
('noix_datanga_bouillie_boiled_bush_butter_nuts_gabonese', 'Noix d''Atanga Bouillie (Boiled Bush Butter Nuts)', 385, 6.4, 13.8, 35.6, 5.4, 2.1, 80, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['noix d''atanga bouillie (boiled bush butter nuts)', 'safou bouilli', 'atanga cuit'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'African pear boiled in salted water until soft and served hot; one of the most nutritious and beloved Gabonese street foods. Rich in essential fatty acids and vitamins, it forms an important part of forest community diets.', TRUE),
('noix_de_palme_grillee_grilled_palm_nuts_gabonese', 'Noix de Palme Grillee (Grilled Palm Nuts)', 341, 4.2, 18.6, 28.4, 6.8, 2.8, 100, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['noix de palme grillee (grilled palm nuts)', 'noix de palme rotie', 'graine de palme grillee'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Fresh palm nuts roasted until charred and served with salt; eaten as a snack throughout palm oil producing regions of Gabon. The nutty smoky flavor is highly prized and the nuts are also pressed for their rich oil.', TRUE),
('snack_de_canne_a_sucre_sugarcane_snack_gabonese', 'Snack de Canne a Sucre (Sugarcane Snack)', 73, 0.4, 18.4, 0.1, 0.6, 17.8, 100, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['snack de canne a sucre (sugarcane snack)', 'canne a sucre fraiche', 'morceau de canne'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Fresh-cut sugarcane stalks chewed for their sweet juice; sold at markets and roadside stalls throughout Gabon. Particularly popular with children who chew the fibrous stalks for the sweet liquid.', TRUE),
('jus_de_canne_frais_fresh_sugarcane_juice_gabonese', 'Jus de Canne Frais (Fresh Sugarcane Juice)', 69, 0.2, 17.2, 0.0, 0.0, 16.8, 250, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['jus de canne frais (fresh sugarcane juice)', 'jus canne sucre', 'vesou frais'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Freshly pressed sugarcane juice served over ice from mechanical crushers at street stalls; a popular refreshment in Libreville''s tropical heat. Often blended with ginger or lime for extra flavor.', TRUE),
('mikate_congolese_style_fried_dough_gabonese', 'Mikate (Congolese-Style Fried Dough)', 392, 6.8, 52.4, 17.4, 1.4, 6.8, 80, 35, 'research', ARRAY['mikate (congolese-style fried dough)', 'beignets congolais', 'makayabu bread'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Soft fried bread rolls similar to Congolese mikate; popular in Gabon especially among the large Congolese expatriate community in Libreville. Eaten for breakfast with sweet coffee or as a snack throughout the day.', TRUE),
('galette_de_mais_corn_flatbread_gabonese', 'Galette de Mais (Corn Flatbread)', 218, 4.8, 42.6, 3.2, 3.4, 2.8, 100, 60, 'research', ARRAY['galette de mais (corn flatbread)', 'pain de mais', 'tortilla de mais gabonaise'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Thick corn flatbread grilled on a hot iron skillet; sold at morning markets and bus stations as a breakfast food. The Gabonese version is often made with white corn flour and seasoned with salt and palm oil.', TRUE),
('beignets_souffles_choux_puffs_gabonese', 'Beignets Souffles (Choux Puffs)', 298, 8.4, 28.6, 16.8, 0.6, 4.2, 80, 25, 'research', ARRAY['beignets souffles (choux puffs)', 'choux a la creme', 'profiteroles gabonais'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Light hollow choux pastry puffs filled with sweet cream or simply dusted with sugar; sold at French-influenced bakeries and street stands in Libreville. Represent the strong French pastry tradition maintained in post-independence Gabon.', TRUE),
('eclairs_au_chocolat_chocolate_eclairs_gabonese', 'Eclairs au Chocolat (Chocolate Eclairs)', 316, 6.8, 36.4, 15.8, 0.8, 18.6, 80, 80, 'research', ARRAY['eclairs au chocolat (chocolate eclairs)', 'eclair chocolat', 'eclair creme'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Classic French chocolate eclairs made with choux pastry filled with custard and topped with chocolate glaze; found at Libreville patisseries. French pastry culture is deeply embedded in urban Gabonese food habits.', TRUE),
('madeleine_a_la_noix_de_coco_coconut_madeleine_gabonese', 'Madeleine a la Noix de Coco (Coconut Madeleine)', 391, 6.8, 54.2, 16.4, 2.1, 32.4, 50, 20, 'research', ARRAY['madeleine a la noix de coco (coconut madeleine)', 'madeleine coco', 'petits gateaux coco'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Shell-shaped French butter cakes made with coconut flour or shredded coconut; produced at artisan bakeries in Libreville. The coconut adaptation of this classic French cookie reflects Gabon''s tropical ingredient palette.', TRUE),
('financier_tropicale_tropical_financier_cake_gabonese', 'Financier Tropicale (Tropical Financier Cake)', 428, 9.2, 48.6, 22.4, 1.4, 34.2, 50, 30, 'research', ARRAY['financier tropicale (tropical financier cake)', 'financier fruit de la passion', 'mini cake amande tropique'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'French almond butter cakes adapted with tropical flavors like passion fruit or mango; found at upscale patisseries in Libreville''s business district. A fusion of French culinary precision with Gabonese tropical ingredients.', TRUE),
('riz_au_lait_de_coco_sucre_sweet_coconut_rice_pudding_gabonese', 'Riz au Lait de Coco Sucre (Sweet Coconut Rice Pudding)', 168, 2.8, 28.6, 5.4, 0.4, 12.8, 200, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['riz au lait de coco sucre (sweet coconut rice pudding)', 'riz lait coco', 'pudding riz coco'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Creamy rice pudding made with coconut milk, cinnamon, and sugar; a comforting dessert served at Gabonese family Sunday lunches. The use of coconut milk instead of dairy reflects Central African culinary adaptation.', TRUE),
('bouillie_de_manioc_sucree_sweet_cassava_porridge_gabonese', 'Bouillie de Manioc Sucree (Sweet Cassava Porridge)', 118, 0.8, 28.4, 0.2, 0.6, 12.4, 250, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['bouillie de manioc sucree (sweet cassava porridge)', 'fufu sucre', 'bouillie manioc', 'colle manioc sucree'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Smooth cassava starch porridge sweetened with sugar and coconut milk; a popular breakfast and dessert in Gabonese households. Known locally as ''fufu sucre'' it is given to children and the elderly as a gentle nourishing food.', TRUE),
('bouillie_darachide_peanut_porridge_gabonese', 'Bouillie d''Arachide (Peanut Porridge)', 186, 7.8, 22.4, 8.6, 2.4, 8.2, 250, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['bouillie d''arachide (peanut porridge)', 'bouillie cacahuete', 'koko arachide'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Thick porridge made from ground peanuts, cornmeal, and sugar; a nutritious breakfast dish also served as dessert in rural Gabon. The combination of groundnuts and grain provides complete protein in remote forest communities.', TRUE),
('gateau_aux_oeufs_gabonese_egg_sponge_cake_gabonese', 'Gateau aux Oeufs (Gabonese Egg Sponge Cake)', 312, 7.2, 48.4, 10.6, 0.4, 28.6, 100, 80, 'research', ARRAY['gateau aux oeufs (gabonese egg sponge cake)', 'genoise gabonaise', 'gateau anniversaire gabonais'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Simple vanilla sponge cake made with eggs, sugar, and flour; the standard celebration cake at Gabonese birthdays and weddings. Often decorated with frosting made from condensed milk and topped with fresh tropical fruits.', TRUE),
('quatre_quarts_tropical_tropical_pound_cake_gabonese', 'Quatre-Quarts Tropical (Tropical Pound Cake)', 394, 6.4, 48.2, 20.4, 0.6, 28.8, 100, 80, 'research', ARRAY['quatre-quarts tropical (tropical pound cake)', 'quatre quarts mangue', 'cake marbré tropique'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Classic French pound cake (quatre-quarts) flavored with passion fruit or mango; baked at Gabonese artisan bakeries and sold by the slice. The tropical fruit flavoring distinguishes the Gabonese version from the traditional French recipe.', TRUE),
('tarte_tatin_a_la_mangue_mango_tarte_tatin_gabonese', 'Tarte Tatin a la Mangue (Mango Tarte Tatin)', 268, 3.4, 42.6, 9.8, 1.4, 26.4, 120, 120, 'research', ARRAY['tarte tatin a la mangue (mango tarte tatin)', 'tatin mangue', 'tarte renversee mangue'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Upside-down caramelized mango tart; a French-influenced dessert made with Gabon''s exceptional sweet mangoes. Served at Libreville restaurants during mango season from December to March.', TRUE),
('pudding_de_pain_gabonais_gabonese_bread_pudding_gabonese', 'Pudding de Pain Gabonais (Gabonese Bread Pudding)', 244, 6.8, 38.4, 7.6, 0.8, 18.6, 150, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['pudding de pain gabonais (gabonese bread pudding)', 'pain perdu sucre', 'pudding pain coco'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Baked bread pudding made with day-old baguette, eggs, condensed milk, and vanilla; a practical Gabonese dessert that minimizes food waste. Often spiced with cinnamon and ginger and soaked in coconut milk.', TRUE),
('churros_gabonais_fried_pastry_sticks_gabonese', 'Churros Gabonais (Fried Pastry Sticks)', 362, 5.6, 52.4, 14.8, 1.2, 12.6, 80, 15, 'research', ARRAY['churros gabonais (fried pastry sticks)', 'beignets pipes', 'churros sucre cannelle'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Piped choux pastry fried until golden and rolled in cinnamon sugar; sold at evening food stalls in Libreville influenced by Spanish and Portuguese colonial food cultures in neighboring countries. Served with chocolate dipping sauce.', TRUE),
('gateau_patate_douce_sweet_potato_cake_gabonese', 'Gateau Patate Douce (Sweet Potato Cake)', 241, 3.8, 44.8, 5.8, 2.2, 24.6, 100, 80, 'research', ARRAY['gateau patate douce (sweet potato cake)', 'cake patate', 'gateau igname douce'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Moist cake made with cooked sweet potato puree, cinnamon, and nutmeg; a rustic Gabonese dessert particularly common in rural areas where sweet potatoes are grown. The natural sweetness reduces the need for added sugar.', TRUE),
('beignets_digname_yam_fritters_gabonese', 'Beignets d''Igname (Yam Fritters)', 198, 2.4, 38.6, 4.2, 3.2, 2.1, 120, 40, 'research', ARRAY['beignets d''igname (yam fritters)', 'galettes d''igname', 'croquettes igname'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Savory yam fritters seasoned with onion, pepper, and salt; fried in palm oil until golden. Sold at morning markets in northern Gabon where yam cultivation is traditional among the Fang and Beti peoples.', TRUE),
('samoussa_gabonais_gabonese_samosa_gabonese', 'Samoussa Gabonais (Gabonese Samosa)', 278, 8.4, 32.8, 12.8, 2.4, 2.6, 80, 30, 'research', ARRAY['samoussa gabonais (gabonese samosa)', 'samosa viande', 'samosa poisson', 'briouats gabonais'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Triangular fried pastry filled with spiced minced meat or fish; introduced by Lebanese and Indian communities in Libreville and now a popular street snack throughout Gabon. Sold at Indian-owned restaurants and street stalls.', TRUE),
('nems_gabonais_gabonese_spring_rolls_gabonese', 'Nems Gabonais (Gabonese Spring Rolls)', 234, 9.8, 26.4, 10.4, 1.8, 2.8, 80, 30, 'research', ARRAY['nems gabonais (gabonese spring rolls)', 'rouleaux frits', 'nems poulet', 'nems legumes'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Fried spring rolls with vegetable and meat filling; reflecting the significant Vietnamese-French influence on Gabonese cuisine. Vietnamese and Chinese immigrants introduced nem to Gabon during the French colonial era.', TRUE),
('brioche_gabonaise_gabonese_brioche_gabonese', 'Brioche Gabonaise (Gabonese Brioche)', 364, 8.6, 48.4, 16.2, 1.2, 12.8, 80, 40, 'research', ARRAY['brioche gabonaise (gabonese brioche)', 'brioche sucrée', 'pain brioché'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Soft enriched bread rolls made with eggs, butter, and sugar; produced at French-trained boulangeries throughout Libreville. The brioche remains one of the most popular breakfast breads in urban Gabon reflecting French colonial legacy.', TRUE),
('pain_au_lait_milk_bread_roll_gabonese', 'Pain au Lait (Milk Bread Roll)', 312, 8.8, 50.4, 8.6, 1.4, 10.2, 80, 40, 'research', ARRAY['pain au lait (milk bread roll)', 'petit pain sucre', 'pain de mie soft'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Soft white bread rolls enriched with milk and sugar; sold at every boulangerie and bakery kiosk in Libreville. A standard breakfast bread eaten with butter and jam or condensed milk in Gabonese households.', TRUE),
('croissant_au_beurre_artisanal_artisan_butter_croissant_gabonese', 'Croissant au Beurre Artisanal (Artisan Butter Croissant)', 406, 8.2, 45.8, 21.4, 1.6, 8.6, 60, 60, 'research', ARRAY['croissant au beurre artisanal (artisan butter croissant)', 'croissant beurre', 'croissant nature'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Laminated buttery pastry made by trained pastry chefs in Libreville''s artisan bakeries; a distinctly French breakfast item that has become central to urban Gabonese breakfast culture since independence.', TRUE),
('pain_au_chocolat_maison_homemade_chocolate_pastry_gabonese', 'Pain au Chocolat Maison (Homemade Chocolate Pastry)', 428, 8.4, 48.6, 22.4, 2.1, 12.8, 60, 60, 'research', ARRAY['pain au chocolat maison (homemade chocolate pastry)', 'chocolatine libreville', 'pain choco'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Laminated pastry encasing a bar of dark chocolate; produced at artisan patisseries in Libreville. Children''s favorite morning pastry in Gabon, reflecting French culinary tradition that persists strongly in post-independence Gabonese urban culture.', TRUE),
('kouign_amann_tropicale_tropical_butter_cake_gabonese', 'Kouign Amann Tropicale (Tropical Butter Cake)', 412, 5.8, 56.4, 18.8, 0.8, 28.4, 100, 80, 'research', ARRAY['kouign amann tropicale (tropical butter cake)', 'gateau beurre caramel', 'kouign coco'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Breton-origin layered butter caramel pastry cake adapted with coconut sugar; made at artisan bakeries in Libreville. The caramelized sugary crust and buttery layers make this a premium dessert at Libreville cafes.', TRUE),
('sable_breton_au_cacao_chocolate_breton_shortbread_gabonese', 'Sable Breton au Cacao (Chocolate Breton Shortbread)', 508, 7.2, 56.8, 28.4, 2.6, 24.8, 50, 15, 'research', ARRAY['sable breton au cacao (chocolate breton shortbread)', 'sable chocolat', 'biscuit sec cacao'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Thick buttery shortbread cookies made with cocoa powder; a Breton-origin cookie produced at French-trained bakeries in Libreville. The cookie culture of France has been fully adopted by urban Gabonese consumers.', TRUE),
('madeleines_au_miel_et_gingembre_honey_ginger_madeleines_gabonese', 'Madeleines au Miel et Gingembre (Honey Ginger Madeleines)', 378, 6.4, 52.8, 15.6, 0.8, 28.4, 50, 20, 'research', ARRAY['madeleines au miel et gingembre (honey ginger madeleines)', 'madeleine miel', 'petits gateaux miel gingembre'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Shell-shaped butter cakes made with Gabonese forest honey and fresh ginger; sold at artisan bakeries and hotel gift shops in Libreville. The combination of local honey and ginger gives these French pastries a distinctly Gabonese character.', TRUE),
('tarte_au_citron_vert_lime_tart_gabonese', 'Tarte au Citron Vert (Lime Tart)', 298, 4.8, 38.4, 14.2, 0.6, 24.8, 100, 100, 'research', ARRAY['tarte au citron vert (lime tart)', 'tarte citron', 'tarte citron meringuee'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'French-style lime tart with a buttery shortcrust pastry and sharp lime curd filling; made at Libreville patisseries using abundant local limes. The tart''s acidity is refreshing in Gabon''s tropical climate.', TRUE),
('cake_marbre_chocolat_vanille_marble_cake_gabonese', 'Cake Marbré Chocolat Vanille (Marble Cake)', 398, 6.4, 50.4, 19.4, 1.2, 26.8, 100, 80, 'research', ARRAY['cake marbré chocolat vanille (marble cake)', 'cake marbré', 'gateau marbre'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Classic marble cake with swirls of vanilla and chocolate batter; a birthday staple at Gabonese bakeries and a popular gift cake for family gatherings. The cake represents French culinary tradition firmly embedded in Gabonese urban culture.', TRUE),
('fondant_au_chocolat_warm_chocolate_lava_cake_gabonese', 'Fondant au Chocolat (Warm Chocolate Lava Cake)', 418, 7.8, 46.4, 22.8, 3.2, 34.6, 80, 80, 'research', ARRAY['fondant au chocolat (warm chocolate lava cake)', 'moelleux chocolat', 'coulant au chocolat'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Warm chocolate cake with a molten center; found at upscale restaurants and hotel restaurants in Libreville. Made with imported dark chocolate from Sao Tome and Principe, showcasing the Gulf of Guinea''s exceptional cacao.', TRUE),
('creme_brulee_a_la_vanille_vanilla_creme_brulee_gabonese', 'Creme Brulee a la Vanille (Vanilla Creme Brulee)', 228, 4.8, 21.6, 13.8, 0.0, 19.4, 120, 120, 'research', ARRAY['creme brulee a la vanille (vanilla creme brulee)', 'brulee vanille', 'creme caramel brulee'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Classic French creme brulee with a caramelized sugar crust; a standard dessert at Libreville''s French-influenced restaurants. Often flavored with local vanilla or passion fruit to give a tropical twist to this colonial-era classic.', TRUE),
('tiramisu_tropical_tropical_tiramisu_gabonese', 'Tiramisu Tropical (Tropical Tiramisu)', 282, 5.6, 28.4, 16.4, 0.4, 18.8, 120, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['tiramisu tropical (tropical tiramisu)', 'tiramisu mangue', 'tiramisu coco café'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Italian-inspired tiramisu made with tropical fruit coulis and locally grown coffee instead of espresso; found at Italian and fusion restaurants in Libreville. Reflects the cosmopolitan dining scene of Gabon''s oil-wealthy capital.', TRUE),
('panna_cotta_au_fruit_de_la_passion_passion_fruit_panna_cotta_gabonese', 'Panna Cotta au Fruit de la Passion (Passion Fruit Panna Cotta)', 182, 3.4, 18.6, 10.8, 0.6, 16.4, 120, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['panna cotta au fruit de la passion (passion fruit panna cotta)', 'panna cotta tropicale', 'blanc manger fruit de passion'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Italian-style panna cotta topped with fresh passion fruit coulis; served at upscale Libreville restaurants. The abundant passion fruit in Gabon gives this dessert an intensely aromatic tropical character.', TRUE),
('sorbet_hibiscus_bissap_sorbet_gabonese', 'Sorbet Hibiscus (Bissap Sorbet)', 96, 0.4, 24.4, 0.1, 0.4, 22.8, 150, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['sorbet hibiscus (bissap sorbet)', 'sorbet bissap', 'granita hibiscus', 'glace fleur de hibiscus'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Refreshing frozen sorbet made from hibiscus (bissap) flower infusion; sold at juice bars and ice cream parlors in Libreville. The deep red color and floral tart flavor make it visually striking and uniquely West-Central African.', TRUE),
('glace_gingembre_citron_ginger_lemon_ice_cream_gabonese', 'Glace Gingembre Citron (Ginger Lemon Ice Cream)', 146, 2.4, 22.8, 5.4, 0.2, 20.4, 100, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['glace gingembre citron (ginger lemon ice cream)', 'glace gingembre', 'ice cream citron gingembre'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Refreshing ice cream made with fresh ginger root and lemon zest; a popular artisan flavor at Libreville ice cream shops. Ginger''s popularity in Gabonese cooking has made it a natural addition to desserts and frozen treats.', TRUE),
('popsicle_coco_coconut_popsicle_gabonese', 'Popsicle Coco (Coconut Popsicle)', 142, 1.2, 18.6, 7.2, 1.4, 16.8, 80, 80, 'research', ARRAY['popsicle coco (coconut popsicle)', 'glace coco sur batonnet', 'popo coco'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Frozen coconut milk and sugar popsicle sold by street vendors from insulated boxes; a cooling street food popular in Libreville''s heat. Simple to make and affordable, coconut popsicles are a childhood staple in Gabonese coastal towns.', TRUE),
('popsicle_mangue_mango_popsicle_gabonese', 'Popsicle Mangue (Mango Popsicle)', 98, 0.6, 24.8, 0.2, 0.8, 22.4, 80, 80, 'research', ARRAY['popsicle mangue (mango popsicle)', 'glace mangue batonnet', 'popo mangue'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Frozen fresh mango juice popsicle; the most popular frozen street snack in Gabon sold by mobile vendors in ice boxes. Made from locally grown mangoes, these are seasonal treats concentrated around January to March mango harvest.', TRUE),
('limonade_de_gingembre_ginger_lemonade_gabonese', 'Limonade de Gingembre (Ginger Lemonade)', 48, 0.1, 12.4, 0.0, 0.1, 11.8, 250, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['limonade de gingembre (ginger lemonade)', 'citronnade gingembre', 'ginger lemon drink'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Cold ginger-infused lemonade made with fresh ginger root, lemon, sugar, and water; sold by street vendors at markets and cultural events throughout Gabon. Considered a healthy digestive and energizing drink.', TRUE),
('jus_bissap_frais_fresh_hibiscus_juice_gabonese', 'Jus Bissap Frais (Fresh Hibiscus Juice)', 62, 0.4, 15.8, 0.1, 0.2, 14.6, 250, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['jus bissap frais (fresh hibiscus juice)', 'bissap sucre', 'the bissap', 'jus fleur de hibiscus'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Cold hibiscus flower infusion sweetened with sugar; sold at street stalls and restaurant throughout Gabon as a refreshing beverage. Known for its deep ruby-red color and tart flavor, bissap is considered a traditional West-Central African health drink.', TRUE),
('tapioca_frit_sucre_sweet_fried_tapioca_gabonese', 'Tapioca Frit Sucre (Sweet Fried Tapioca)', 242, 0.4, 52.8, 4.8, 0.6, 12.4, 80, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['tapioca frit sucre (sweet fried tapioca)', 'tapioca frit', 'amidon frit sucre'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Tapioca pearls or cassava starch cakes fried in oil and sprinkled with sugar; a simple street snack sold at Gabonese markets. The chewy texture and sweet coating make it an affordable treat for all ages.', TRUE),
('boules_de_sesame_sucre_sweet_sesame_balls_gabonese', 'Boules de Sesame Sucre (Sweet Sesame Balls)', 478, 10.4, 58.4, 22.6, 4.8, 28.6, 50, 15, 'research', ARRAY['boules de sesame sucre (sweet sesame balls)', 'barre sesame', 'croquant sesame', 'sesame sukari'], 'candy', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Sesame seeds bound with caramelized sugar into balls or bars; a traditional confection sold at Central African markets. The high sesame content provides good nutrition making these a popular energy snack.', TRUE),
('croquettes_de_riz_sucre_sweet_rice_croquettes_gabonese', 'Croquettes de Riz Sucre (Sweet Rice Croquettes)', 212, 3.8, 40.4, 4.2, 0.6, 14.8, 80, 30, 'research', ARRAY['croquettes de riz sucre (sweet rice croquettes)', 'boules de riz sucre', 'riz frit sucre'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Fried rice balls coated in coconut sugar; a street snack sold at markets and sold as an affordable sweet treat. The use of leftover rice makes these an economical and popular staple of Gabonese market food culture.', TRUE),
('gateaux_secs_aux_raisins_raisin_cookies_gabonese', 'Gateaux Secs aux Raisins (Raisin Cookies)', 416, 5.8, 68.4, 13.4, 2.4, 32.8, 50, 15, 'research', ARRAY['gateaux secs aux raisins (raisin cookies)', 'biscuits raisins secs', 'sable aux raisins'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Dry shortbread cookies studded with raisins; sold at bakeries and corner stores throughout Libreville. A popular snack for schoolchildren eaten with sweet tea, representing French cookie traditions adapted for Gabonese tastes.', TRUE),
('gateau_sec_a_la_vanille_vanilla_shortbread_gabonese', 'Gateau Sec a la Vanille (Vanilla Shortbread)', 468, 5.6, 62.4, 22.4, 0.8, 24.6, 50, 12, 'research', ARRAY['gateau sec a la vanille (vanilla shortbread)', 'sable vanille', 'biscuit beurre vanille'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Classic French-style vanilla butter cookies; one of the most common biscuits found at Gabonese tea time and sold in tins at supermarkets. Simple yet beloved, these cookies are a standard accompaniment to coffee and tea throughout Gabon.', TRUE),
('tartine_beurre_cacahuete_peanut_butter_toast_gabonese', 'Tartine Beurre Cacahuete (Peanut Butter Toast)', 348, 12.8, 32.4, 19.8, 2.8, 6.4, 100, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['tartine beurre cacahuete (peanut butter toast)', 'pain beurre arachide', 'toast cacahuete'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Baguette slices spread with thick homemade peanut butter; a common Gabonese breakfast and street snack. Peanut butter is often made fresh at markets by grinding roasted peanuts using mechanical mills.', TRUE),
('sandwich_thon_avocat_tuna_avocado_sandwich_gabonese', 'Sandwich Thon Avocat (Tuna Avocado Sandwich)', 286, 16.4, 26.8, 13.2, 3.8, 2.4, 200, 200, 'research', ARRAY['sandwich thon avocat (tuna avocado sandwich)', 'sandwich avocat thon', 'baguette thon avocat'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Baguette sandwich filled with canned tuna and fresh avocado; a popular lunchtime street food in Libreville''s business district. Avocados grow abundantly in Gabon and this sandwich reflects the French sandwich culture adapted with tropical ingredients.', TRUE),
('sandwich_poulet_mayo_chicken_mayonnaise_sandwich_gabonese', 'Sandwich Poulet Mayo (Chicken Mayonnaise Sandwich)', 312, 18.4, 28.6, 13.8, 1.2, 3.2, 200, 200, 'research', ARRAY['sandwich poulet mayo (chicken mayonnaise sandwich)', 'baguette poulet mayo', 'sandwich poulet salade'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Baguette filled with shredded roasted chicken, mayonnaise, and lettuce; sold at sandwich stalls near offices and schools in Libreville. A quick lunchtime option reflecting the French-influenced fast food culture of urban Gabon.', TRUE),
('hot_dog_gabonais_gabonese_hot_dog_gabonese', 'Hot Dog Gabonais (Gabonese Hot Dog)', 296, 12.8, 26.4, 15.4, 1.2, 4.8, 150, 150, 'research', ARRAY['hot dog gabonais (gabonese hot dog)', 'saucisse baguette', 'hot dog libreville'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Sausage in a bun with mustard, ketchup, and fried onions; sold at street kiosks in Libreville and Port-Gentil. A global street food that has been adopted into Gabonese urban food culture especially in oil industry towns.', TRUE),
('burger_gabonais_gabonese_beef_burger_gabonese', 'Burger Gabonais (Gabonese Beef Burger)', 378, 18.6, 28.8, 21.4, 1.6, 5.8, 200, 200, 'research', ARRAY['burger gabonais (gabonese beef burger)', 'burger boeuf pili-pili', 'burger africain'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Beef burger with local spices, caramelized onions, and chili sauce served in a brioche bun; sold at fast food stalls and small restaurants in Libreville. The Gabonese adaptation adds pili-pili sauce and sometimes fried plantain.', TRUE),
('pizza_libreville_libreville_street_pizza_gabonese', 'Pizza Libreville (Libreville Street Pizza)', 271, 11.2, 32.6, 10.8, 1.8, 4.2, 200, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['pizza libreville (libreville street pizza)', 'pizza poisson fume', 'pizza gabonaise', 'pizza africaine'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Individual thin-crust pizza topped with local ingredients including smoked fish, palm heart, and spicy sauce; sold at pizza stalls in Libreville. Pizza culture arrived with Italian oil workers and has been enthusiastically adapted.', TRUE),
('frites_patate_sweet_potato_fries_gabonese', 'Frites Patate (Sweet Potato Fries)', 148, 2.2, 28.6, 4.8, 3.4, 6.8, 150, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['frites patate (sweet potato fries)', 'frites de patate douce', 'chips patate'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Sweet potato strips fried in palm oil and seasoned with salt and pili-pili; a popular side dish served alongside grilled meats at Gabonese street food stalls. The orange-fleshed variety gives a natural sweetness and beta-carotene richness.', TRUE),
('poisson_fume_en_papillote_smoked_fish_parcel_gabonese', 'Poisson Fume en Papillote (Smoked Fish Parcel)', 186, 28.4, 2.4, 6.8, 0.4, 1.2, 100, 100, 'research', ARRAY['poisson fume en papillote (smoked fish parcel)', 'maboke poisson fume', 'poisson fume enveloppe'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Smoked fish wrapped in banana leaves and briefly reheated over charcoal; sold as a portable street snack at markets throughout Gabon. A traditional food preservation and preparation technique of the Gabonese Bantu peoples.', TRUE),
('crevettes_grillees_pili_pili_pili_pili_grilled_shrimp_gabonese', 'Crevettes Grillees Pili-Pili (Pili-Pili Grilled Shrimp)', 128, 22.4, 1.8, 3.6, 0.2, 0.4, 150, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['crevettes grillees pili-pili (pili-pili grilled shrimp)', 'brochettes crevettes pili', 'gambas pili-pili'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Fresh Atlantic shrimp skewered and grilled with pili-pili chili marinade; sold at beach barbecue stalls along the Atlantic coast. Gabon''s 800km coastline provides abundant fresh shrimp that are a staple of coastal street food.', TRUE),
('poisson_grille_entier_avec_sauce_moutarde_whole_grilled_fish_mustard_gabonese', 'Poisson Grille Entier avec Sauce Moutarde (Whole Grilled Fish Mustard)', 162, 24.8, 2.4, 5.8, 0.2, 1.4, 200, 200, 'research', ARRAY['poisson grille entier avec sauce moutarde (whole grilled fish mustard)', 'capitaine moutarde grille', 'tilapia grille moutarde'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Whole grilled fish marinated in mustard, lemon, and herbs; sold at roadside braai stalls. The French influence in Gabonese marinade culture is reflected in the use of Dijon-style mustard with local pili-pili pepper.', TRUE),
('poulet_braise_au_gingembre_ginger_braised_chicken_gabonese', 'Poulet Braise au Gingembre (Ginger Braised Chicken)', 198, 28.4, 4.2, 7.8, 0.4, 2.8, 200, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['poulet braise au gingembre (ginger braised chicken)', 'poulet gingembre braise', 'chicken braise gingembre'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Chicken marinated in fresh ginger, garlic, and pili-pili then braised over charcoal; sold at busy street-corner stalls throughout Gabon. The ginger marinade is a signature of Gabonese braised chicken distinct from Ivoirian or Congolese styles.', TRUE),
('samosa_aux_crevettes_shrimp_samosa_gabonese', 'Samosa aux Crevettes (Shrimp Samosa)', 264, 9.6, 28.4, 12.4, 1.8, 2.2, 80, 30, 'research', ARRAY['samosa aux crevettes (shrimp samosa)', 'samoussa crevettes', 'briouats crevettes'], 'appetizer', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Crispy fried pastry filled with spiced shrimp and vegetables; influenced by Lebanese and Indian communities in Libreville. A popular appetizer at Gabonese parties and sold as street food near Lebanese restaurants in Libreville.', TRUE),
('bruschetta_a_lavocat_avocado_bruschetta_gabonese', 'Bruschetta a l''Avocat (Avocado Bruschetta)', 218, 4.8, 22.6, 12.4, 4.8, 2.4, 100, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['bruschetta a l''avocat (avocado bruschetta)', 'toast avocat', 'tartine avocat'], 'appetizer', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Toasted baguette topped with mashed avocado, tomato, and lemon; an appetizer at Libreville''s modern cafes and bistros. Avocados are grown in abundance in Gabon making this a locally sourced adaptation of the Italian bruschetta.', TRUE),
('carpaccio_davocat_et_crevettes_avocado_shrimp_carpaccio_gabonese', 'Carpaccio d''Avocat et Crevettes (Avocado Shrimp Carpaccio)', 168, 12.4, 6.8, 11.2, 3.6, 2.1, 120, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['carpaccio d''avocat et crevettes (avocado shrimp carpaccio)', 'avocat crevettes vinaigrette', 'cocktail avocat gambas'], 'appetizer', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Thinly sliced avocado layered with poached shrimp and citrus vinaigrette; a refined appetizer at Libreville fine dining restaurants. The combination of local avocado and Atlantic shrimp showcases Gabon''s coastal bounty.', TRUE),
('veloute_de_manioc_creamy_cassava_soup_gabonese', 'Veloute de Manioc (Creamy Cassava Soup)', 128, 1.6, 24.8, 3.4, 1.2, 2.8, 250, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['veloute de manioc (creamy cassava soup)', 'soupe manioc', 'creme de manioc'], 'appetizer', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Smooth velvety cassava soup with coconut milk and ginger; served as a starter at modern Gabonese restaurants. A sophisticated presentation of the country''s staple crop, cassava, elevated to fine dining standard.', TRUE),
('veloute_de_plantain_plantain_soup_gabonese', 'Veloute de Plantain (Plantain Soup)', 112, 1.8, 22.4, 2.8, 1.8, 6.4, 250, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['veloute de plantain (plantain soup)', 'soupe plantain', 'creme de banane plantain'], 'appetizer', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Smooth soup made from ripe plantains blended with coconut milk and spices; a creative appetizer at modern Gabonese restaurants. The natural sweetness of ripe plantain creates a distinct savory-sweet soup unique to Central African cuisine.', TRUE),
('terrine_de_poisson_fume_smoked_fish_terrine_gabonese', 'Terrine de Poisson Fumé (Smoked Fish Terrine)', 168, 16.8, 4.2, 9.4, 0.4, 1.8, 80, 80, 'research', ARRAY['terrine de poisson fumé (smoked fish terrine)', 'pate de poisson fume', 'rillettes de poisson'], 'appetizer', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Pressed terrine of flaked smoked fish bound with eggs and herbs; a French-influenced starter at upscale restaurants in Libreville. Smoked fish is a fundamental Gabonese ingredient elevated here to French charcuterie technique.', TRUE),
('salade_caprese_tropicale_tropical_caprese_salad_gabonese', 'Salade Caprese Tropicale (Tropical Caprese Salad)', 148, 6.8, 8.4, 9.8, 1.2, 6.4, 150, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['salade caprese tropicale (tropical caprese salad)', 'caprese mangue', 'salade mozzarella mangue'], 'appetizer', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Tropical adaptation of Caprese salad with mango, fresh mozzarella, and mint; served at Italian-influenced restaurants in Libreville. The substitution of ripe mango for tomato creates a uniquely Gabonese take on this classic Italian starter.', TRUE),
('tartare_davocat_et_mangue_avocado_mango_tartare_gabonese', 'Tartare d''Avocat et Mangue (Avocado Mango Tartare)', 142, 2.4, 14.8, 9.4, 4.8, 8.6, 120, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['tartare d''avocat et mangue (avocado mango tartare)', 'tartare avocat mangue', 'ceviche avocat mangue'], 'appetizer', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Diced avocado and mango seasoned with lime, chili, and coriander; a refreshing appetizer popular at Libreville''s modern restaurants. The combination of Gabon''s finest produce—avocado and mango—makes this a quintessential Gabonese fusion starter.', TRUE),
('ceviche_de_capitaine_nile_perch_ceviche_gabonese', 'Ceviche de Capitaine (Nile Perch Ceviche)', 128, 18.6, 6.4, 2.8, 0.8, 3.4, 150, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['ceviche de capitaine (nile perch ceviche)', 'ceviche poisson', 'poisson cru au citron'], 'appetizer', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Raw Nile perch marinated in citrus juice with onion, coriander, and chili; a South American-influenced appetizer adapted at Libreville''s cosmopolitan restaurants. The citrus cure reflects the fish preparation techniques of Gabon''s coastal fishing communities.', TRUE),
('plateau_de_fruits_de_mer_seafood_platter_gabonese', 'Plateau de Fruits de Mer (Seafood Platter)', 118, 20.4, 3.8, 2.4, 0.0, 0.4, 200, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['plateau de fruits de mer (seafood platter)', 'plateau fruits mer', 'assiette fruits mer'], 'appetizer', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Mixed platter of fresh Atlantic seafood including shrimp, crab claws, and oysters; served at coastal restaurants in Libreville and Port-Gentil. Gabon''s Atlantic coast yields exceptional seafood enjoyed at upscale ocean-view restaurants.', TRUE),
('accras_de_morue_salt_cod_fritters_gabonese', 'Accras de Morue (Salt Cod Fritters)', 264, 12.8, 24.6, 12.4, 1.2, 1.8, 80, 20, 'research', ARRAY['accras de morue (salt cod fritters)', 'beignets morue', 'acras gabonais'], 'appetizer', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Caribbean-influenced salt cod fritters seasoned with herbs, onion, and chili; a popular appetizer in Libreville reflecting the significant Antillean community presence. French Caribbean cuisine has been influential in Gabonese French-influenced cooking.', TRUE),
('rillettes_de_poisson_fume_smoked_fish_rillettes_gabonese', 'Rillettes de Poisson Fumé (Smoked Fish Rillettes)', 312, 18.4, 1.4, 24.8, 0.2, 0.8, 60, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['rillettes de poisson fumé (smoked fish rillettes)', 'pate de poisson tartinable', 'mousse poisson fume'], 'appetizer', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Spreadable smoked fish pate blended with butter and herbs; served on toast points at Libreville bistros. This French charcuterie technique applied to Gabonese smoked fish creates a unique Gabono-French appetizer.', TRUE),
('soupe_de_coco_et_gambas_coconut_shrimp_soup_gabonese', 'Soupe de Coco et Gambas (Coconut Shrimp Soup)', 142, 12.4, 8.6, 7.4, 1.2, 4.8, 250, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['soupe de coco et gambas (coconut shrimp soup)', 'tom kha gambas gabonais', 'soupe coco crevettes'], 'appetizer', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Fragrant soup made with coconut milk, galangal, and Atlantic prawns; a Thai-influenced soup adapted at Libreville international restaurants. Reflects the cosmopolitan dining culture of Gabon''s oil-wealthy capital.', TRUE),
('feuillete_de_palme_palm_heart_puff_pastry_gabonese', 'Feuillete de Palme (Palm Heart Puff Pastry)', 318, 6.4, 26.8, 20.4, 1.8, 2.4, 80, 80, 'research', ARRAY['feuillete de palme (palm heart puff pastry)', 'chausson coeur de palmier', 'pastilla palme'], 'appetizer', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Puff pastry parcel filled with sauteed palm heart and cream cheese; an upscale appetizer at Libreville fine dining restaurants. Palm heart (coeur de palmier) is harvested from Gabon''s abundant palm forests and is considered a delicacy.', TRUE),
('tapenade_olives_et_piment_olive_chili_tapenade_gabonese', 'Tapenade Olives et Piment (Olive Chili Tapenade)', 186, 1.8, 6.4, 16.8, 3.2, 1.2, 30, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['tapenade olives et piment (olive chili tapenade)', 'tapenade pili-pili', 'pate d''olive pimente'], 'appetizer', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Pureed black olives with pili-pili chili and capers; served with bread at French-influenced restaurants in Libreville. The addition of pili-pili to the French Provencal classic makes this a distinctly Gabonese adaptation.', TRUE),
('gateau_de_crevettes_shrimp_cake_gabonese', 'Gateau de Crevettes (Shrimp Cake)', 198, 16.8, 12.4, 8.6, 0.8, 2.4, 100, 80, 'research', ARRAY['gateau de crevettes (shrimp cake)', 'cake crevettes', 'flan de crevettes'], 'appetizer', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Savory shrimp and vegetable cake baked in a mold; a refined appetizer at Libreville restaurants. The abundance of Atlantic shrimp in Gabon makes this an economical yet elegant starter that showcases coastal seafood.', TRUE),
('flamme_de_manioc_cassava_flambe_appetizer_gabonese', 'Flamme de Manioc (Cassava Flambe Appetizer)', 228, 2.4, 38.6, 7.8, 2.4, 6.8, 100, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['flamme de manioc (cassava flambe appetizer)', 'chips manioc sauce palme', 'crackers manioc'], 'appetizer', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Cassava chips baked thin and served with a palm oil and herb dipping sauce; a creative appetizer at modern Gabonese restaurants reinventing traditional ingredients. Represents the new wave of Gabonese haute cuisine.', TRUE),
('salade_datanga_et_feta_bush_butter_and_feta_salad_gabonese', 'Salade d''Atanga et Feta (Bush Butter and Feta Salad)', 248, 7.8, 8.4, 20.6, 4.8, 3.2, 120, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['salade d''atanga et feta (bush butter and feta salad)', 'salade safou feta', 'atanga cheese salad'], 'appetizer', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'African pear (atanga/safou) combined with Greek feta cheese, mint, and lemon; a fusion appetizer at Libreville''s creative restaurants. Lebanese and Mediterranean communities in Libreville have influenced this cross-cultural salad.', TRUE),
('bruschetta_poisson_fume_smoked_fish_bruschetta_gabonese', 'Bruschetta Poisson Fumé (Smoked Fish Bruschetta)', 218, 14.8, 22.4, 7.8, 1.4, 2.6, 100, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['bruschetta poisson fumé (smoked fish bruschetta)', 'toast poisson fume avocat', 'tartine poisson fume'], 'appetizer', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Toasted baguette topped with flaked smoked tilapia, avocado cream, and lime; a popular appetizer at modern Libreville cafes. The pairing of Gabon''s smoked fish tradition with French bruschetta technique creates a distinctive local specialty.', TRUE),
('croque_monsieur_gabonais_gabonese_croque_monsieur_gabonese', 'Croque-Monsieur Gabonais (Gabonese Croque Monsieur)', 348, 16.8, 28.4, 18.6, 1.2, 3.8, 150, 150, 'research', ARRAY['croque-monsieur gabonais (gabonese croque monsieur)', 'croque monsieur', 'toast fromage jambon'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Toasted ham and cheese sandwich with bechamel; served at French-influenced cafes in Libreville. A standard French brasserie item that has been fully adopted into Gabonese cafe culture since the colonial era.', TRUE),
('omelette_au_poisson_fume_smoked_fish_omelette_gabonese', 'Omelette au Poisson Fumé (Smoked Fish Omelette)', 198, 16.8, 2.4, 14.2, 0.4, 1.8, 150, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['omelette au poisson fumé (smoked fish omelette)', 'omelette poisson', 'omelette gabonaise'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Fluffy omelette filled with flaked smoked fish and spring onions; sold at breakfast stalls and small restaurants throughout Gabon. The smoked fish omelette is a practical and nutritious street breakfast combining French cooking technique with Gabonese ingredients.', TRUE),
('tarte_a_latanga_bush_butter_fruit_tart_gabonese', 'Tarte a l''Atanga (Bush Butter Fruit Tart)', 312, 4.8, 28.6, 20.4, 5.2, 8.4, 100, 80, 'research', ARRAY['tarte a l''atanga (bush butter fruit tart)', 'tarte safou', 'flan atanga'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Savory tart shell filled with pureed atanga/safou; a creative dessert at modern Gabonese restaurants showcasing the unique flavor of this native fruit. The rich buttery taste of safou naturally lends itself to pastry applications.', TRUE),
('pudding_de_coco_coconut_steamed_pudding_gabonese', 'Pudding de Coco (Coconut Steamed Pudding)', 262, 4.6, 36.4, 11.8, 2.4, 24.8, 150, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['pudding de coco (coconut steamed pudding)', 'pudding coco vapeur', 'gateau vapeur coco'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Steamed coconut pudding served warm with caramel sauce; a traditional dessert from Gabonese coastal communities where coconut trees are abundant. Slow steaming in a bain-marie gives this pudding its characteristic dense moist texture.', TRUE),
('beignets_de_ananas_pineapple_fritters_gabonese', 'Beignets de Ananas (Pineapple Fritters)', 198, 2.4, 34.8, 6.4, 1.4, 18.6, 100, 35, 'research', ARRAY['beignets de ananas (pineapple fritters)', 'ananas frit', 'rondelles d''ananas frites'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Fresh pineapple rings dipped in batter and deep-fried, dusted with cinnamon sugar; sold at dessert stalls in Libreville evening markets. Gabonese pineapples from the Nyanga province are among the sweetest in Central Africa.', TRUE),
('pate_de_fruit_tropicale_tropical_fruit_paste_gabonese', 'Pate de Fruit Tropicale (Tropical Fruit Paste)', 318, 0.6, 78.4, 0.2, 2.8, 64.8, 30, 15, 'research', ARRAY['pate de fruit tropicale (tropical fruit paste)', 'pate de goyave', 'pate de mangue', 'fruit candy tropical'], 'candy', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Concentrated fruit paste candies made from guava, mango, or passion fruit; a traditional African confection made by boiling fruit pulp with sugar until thick. Sold wrapped in cellophane at market stalls and sweet shops.', TRUE),
('confiserie_papaye_papaya_confection_gabonese', 'Confiserie Papaye (Papaya Confection)', 284, 0.8, 72.4, 0.4, 1.8, 58.6, 30, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['confiserie papaye (papaya confection)', 'papaye confite', 'papaye cristallisee', 'papaye sechee sucree'], 'candy', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Dried and sugar-preserved papaya pieces or papaya fruit leather; sold at market stalls throughout Gabon. Green papaya is simmered with sugar until translucent to make a traditional Gabonese sweet preserve eaten as candy.', TRUE),
('ecorces_dorange_confites_candied_orange_peel_gabonese', 'Ecorces d''Orange Confites (Candied Orange Peel)', 316, 0.8, 82.4, 0.2, 4.2, 68.6, 20, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['ecorces d''orange confites (candied orange peel)', 'zestes d''orange confits', 'orange confit'], 'candy', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Orange peel slowly simmered in sugar syrup until tender and then dried; a French confectionery technique practiced by Libreville artisan confectioners. Made from oranges grown in Gabon''s northern provinces.', TRUE),
('gombo_frit_croustillant_crispy_fried_okra_gabonese', 'Gombo Frit Croustillant (Crispy Fried Okra)', 168, 4.8, 18.4, 8.4, 5.8, 1.8, 100, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['gombo frit croustillant (crispy fried okra)', 'chips de gombo', 'okra frit'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Sliced okra coated in spiced flour and deep-fried until crispy; a popular snack at Gabonese markets and restaurants. Okra is a cornerstone vegetable in Gabonese cooking and the fried version transforms it into an addictive snack.', TRUE),
('noix_de_kola_fraiche_fresh_kola_nut_gabonese', 'Noix de Kola Fraiche (Fresh Kola Nut)', 228, 3.4, 48.2, 1.2, 2.8, 2.4, 20, 10, 'research', ARRAY['noix de kola fraiche (fresh kola nut)', 'kola amere', 'noix cola'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Bitter kola nut chewed for its caffeine and theobromine stimulant properties; offered as a sign of hospitality and used in traditional ceremonies throughout Gabon. Kola nuts are central to Gabonese and broader Central African social and spiritual customs.', TRUE),
('piment_frais_en_collation_fresh_chili_snack_gabonese', 'Piment Frais en Collation (Fresh Chili Snack)', 40, 1.8, 8.8, 0.4, 1.4, 4.6, 30, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['piment frais en collation (fresh chili snack)', 'pili-pili frais', 'piment cru snack'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Fresh pili-pili peppers eaten whole as a snack or condiment by chili-loving Gabonese; a test of strength at social gatherings. The Gabonese pili-pili is among the hottest in Central Africa and is eaten fresh by those who can tolerate the heat.', TRUE),
('noix_de_macadamia_grillee_roasted_macadamia_gabonese', 'Noix de Macadamia Grillee (Roasted Macadamia)', 718, 7.9, 13.8, 75.8, 8.6, 4.6, 30, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['noix de macadamia grillee (roasted macadamia)', 'macadamia salee', 'noix macadamia rotie'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Dry-roasted macadamia nuts sold at premium food shops in Libreville; macadamia farming has been introduced as a cash crop in Gabon''s agricultural diversification programs. Found at supermarkets targeting the expatriate and upper-class Gabonese market.', TRUE),
('mix_de_noix_tropicales_tropical_nut_mix_gabonese', 'Mix de Noix Tropicales (Tropical Nut Mix)', 584, 15.4, 22.8, 50.4, 6.8, 8.6, 40, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['mix de noix tropicales (tropical nut mix)', 'melange de noix', 'trail mix gabonais'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Mixed bag of roasted peanuts, cashews, and dried coconut chips; sold in pre-packaged bags at Gabonese supermarkets and convenience stores. A modern snack product reflecting the emergence of packaged food culture in urban Gabon.', TRUE),
('popcorn_sucre_au_coco_sweet_coconut_popcorn_gabonese', 'Popcorn Sucre au Coco (Sweet Coconut Popcorn)', 394, 5.2, 68.4, 11.8, 6.4, 24.6, 50, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['popcorn sucre au coco (sweet coconut popcorn)', 'popcorn coco', 'maïs eclate coco sucre'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Popcorn drizzled with coconut caramel; sold at cinemas and street stalls in Libreville. Popcorn is a popular modern snack in Gabon and the coconut caramel version reflects local flavor preferences.', TRUE),
('popcorn_pili_pili_spicy_popcorn_gabonese', 'Popcorn Pili-Pili (Spicy Popcorn)', 378, 6.8, 68.2, 8.4, 6.8, 1.2, 50, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['popcorn pili-pili (spicy popcorn)', 'popcorn piment', 'mais eclate pili'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Popcorn seasoned with dried pili-pili chili and salt; a popular movie-time and market snack in Libreville. The pili-pili spicing reflects Gabon''s love of heat in all foods including snacks.', TRUE),
('chips_de_banane_sucree_sweet_banana_chips_gabonese', 'Chips de Banane Sucrée (Sweet Banana Chips)', 484, 2.4, 64.8, 23.8, 3.8, 36.4, 40, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['chips de banane sucrée (sweet banana chips)', 'chips banane frites sucrees', 'banana chips coco'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Dried ripe banana slices fried in coconut oil and lightly sweetened; sold in small packets at kiosks. Made from Gabon''s abundant banana varieties, these chips are a convenient packaged form of the beloved fried plantain snack.', TRUE),
('crackers_de_manioc_aux_herbes_herb_cassava_crackers_gabonese', 'Crackers de Manioc aux Herbes (Herb Cassava Crackers)', 382, 1.8, 78.4, 6.2, 2.4, 1.4, 30, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['crackers de manioc aux herbes (herb cassava crackers)', 'crackers manioc', 'biscuits manioc herbes'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Thin crispy cassava crackers seasoned with dried herbs and palm oil; an artisanal snack product from Gabonese food SMEs. A healthier and locally-sourced alternative to wheat-based crackers, they are sold at organic and artisan food markets.', TRUE),
('gateau_au_fromage_tropical_tropical_cheesecake_gabonese', 'Gateau au Fromage Tropical (Tropical Cheesecake)', 326, 7.2, 28.6, 20.4, 0.8, 22.4, 120, 120, 'research', ARRAY['gateau au fromage tropical (tropical cheesecake)', 'cheesecake tropical', 'cheesecake mangue passion'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Cream cheese cheesecake with a tropical fruit topping of passion fruit and mango; found at Libreville''s upscale patisseries. The American-inspired dessert has been enthusiastically adopted and tropicalized by Gabonese pastry chefs.', TRUE),
('verrines_de_fruits_tropicaux_tropical_fruit_verrine_gabonese', 'Verrines de Fruits Tropicaux (Tropical Fruit Verrine)', 112, 2.4, 22.6, 2.8, 2.4, 18.4, 150, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['verrines de fruits tropicaux (tropical fruit verrine)', 'verrine tropicale', 'coupe de fruits tropicaux'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Layered dessert cups with tropical fruits, yogurt, and coconut cream; a modern dessert presentation popular at Libreville catered events and restaurants. The verrine format allows showcasing multiple Gabonese fruits in a single elegant serving.', TRUE),
('macaron_a_la_noix_de_coco_coconut_macaroon_gabonese', 'Macaron a la Noix de Coco (Coconut Macaroon)', 466, 5.4, 58.6, 23.8, 4.2, 48.4, 40, 15, 'research', ARRAY['macaron a la noix de coco (coconut macaroon)', 'congolais coco', 'rocher coco'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Moist coconut macaroon cookie made with shredded coconut and egg white; produced at Libreville bakeries. Not to be confused with the French macaron, these are denser coconut cookies that have become a popular everyday sweet.', TRUE),
('tropezienne_libreville_cream_filled_brioche_gabonese', 'Tropezienne Libreville (Cream-Filled Brioche)', 368, 7.8, 44.8, 17.4, 0.8, 16.8, 100, 100, 'research', ARRAY['tropezienne libreville (cream-filled brioche)', 'tarte tropezienne', 'brioche crème'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Brioche filled with cream pastry and topped with pearl sugar; a French Riviera pastry found at Libreville''s best patisseries. The tarte tropezienne has become a signature dessert at Gabon''s French-trained pastry establishments.', TRUE),
('charlotte_aux_fruits_charlotte_fruit_dessert_gabonese', 'Charlotte aux Fruits (Charlotte Fruit Dessert)', 262, 5.8, 38.6, 9.4, 1.8, 24.8, 150, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['charlotte aux fruits (charlotte fruit dessert)', 'charlotte tropicale', 'charlotte mangue'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Ladyfinger biscuits lining a mold filled with fruit mousse; a classic French dessert made with tropical fruits at Libreville celebrations. Typically made with mango or passion fruit mousse, this elegant dessert is served at Gabonese wedding receptions.', TRUE),
('gateau_mousseline_citron_vert_lime_chiffon_cake_gabonese', 'Gateau Mousseline Citron Vert (Lime Chiffon Cake)', 296, 6.4, 48.8, 8.4, 0.4, 28.6, 100, 80, 'research', ARRAY['gateau mousseline citron vert (lime chiffon cake)', 'chiffon citron vert', 'cake mousseline lime'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Light airy chiffon cake flavored with fresh lime juice and zest; a popular birthday and celebration cake at Libreville patisseries. Lime grows abundantly in Gabon and its refreshing acidity is appreciated in Gabon''s hot tropical climate.', TRUE),
('entremet_chocolat_et_coco_chocolate_coconut_entremet_gabonese', 'Entremet Chocolat et Coco (Chocolate Coconut Entremet)', 358, 6.8, 34.6, 22.4, 4.2, 26.8, 120, 120, 'research', ARRAY['entremet chocolat et coco (chocolate coconut entremet)', 'bavarois chocolat coco', 'mousse cake chocolate coco'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Multi-layered mousse cake combining dark chocolate and coconut cream; a showstopper dessert at Libreville''s premium patisseries. Dark chocolate from Sao Tome and fresh Gabonese coconut create an exceptional flavor combination.', TRUE),
('galette_des_rois_tropicale_tropical_king_cake_gabonese', 'Galette des Rois Tropicale (Tropical King Cake)', 438, 7.6, 42.8, 27.4, 1.8, 18.6, 120, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['galette des rois tropicale (tropical king cake)', 'galette frangipane coco', 'galette epiphanie tropicale'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Puff pastry cake filled with frangipane cream flavored with coconut or mango; made at Libreville patisseries in January for Epiphany. The French tradition of galette des rois has been enthusiastically adopted and tropicalized in Gabon.', TRUE),
('buche_de_noel_gabonaise_gabonese_yule_log_gabonese', 'Buche de Noel Gabonaise (Gabonese Yule Log)', 348, 6.4, 42.8, 17.8, 2.4, 28.6, 120, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['buche de noel gabonaise (gabonese yule log)', 'buche coco passion', 'buche noel tropicale'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Christmas yule log cake adapted with tropical flavors like coconut and passion fruit; made at Libreville patisseries during the festive season. Christmas is widely celebrated in predominantly Christian Gabon, making this a seasonal specialty.', TRUE),
('pop_cake_mangue_mango_cake_pop_gabonese', 'Pop Cake Mangue (Mango Cake Pop)', 386, 4.8, 54.6, 17.4, 1.2, 36.8, 50, 30, 'research', ARRAY['pop cake mangue (mango cake pop)', 'cake pop tropical', 'boule gateau mangue'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Mango-flavored cake rolled into balls and dipped in white chocolate; a modern confection sold at Libreville bakeries targeting the younger urban market. Cake pops represent the adoption of American patisserie trends in Gabonese food culture.', TRUE),
('waffles_de_mais_corn_waffles_gabonese', 'Waffles de Mais (Corn Waffles)', 268, 5.8, 44.8, 7.4, 2.8, 6.4, 100, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['waffles de mais (corn waffles)', 'gaufres mais', 'waffle maïs'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Crispy waffles made with corn flour and served with palm sugar syrup; a breakfast or snack item at modern Libreville street food stalls. The corn waffle reflects attempts to incorporate traditional African grains into modern street food formats.', TRUE),
('papaye_farcie_sucree_sweet_stuffed_papaya_gabonese', 'Papaye Farcie Sucrée (Sweet Stuffed Papaya)', 112, 1.8, 26.4, 0.6, 2.8, 18.6, 200, 200, 'research', ARRAY['papaye farcie sucrée (sweet stuffed papaya)', 'papaye farcie aux fruits', 'bateau de papaye'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Ripe papaya halved and filled with a mixture of fruit salad and coconut cream; a simple fresh dessert served at Gabonese family lunches. The natural bowl of the papaya makes this a practical and visually appealing fruit dessert.', TRUE),
('ananas_roti_au_caramel_caramelized_roasted_pineapple_gabonese', 'Ananas Roti au Caramel (Caramelized Roasted Pineapple)', 108, 0.6, 26.8, 0.4, 1.4, 22.4, 150, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['ananas roti au caramel (caramelized roasted pineapple)', 'ananas caramelise', 'pineapple flambe'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Pineapple slices caramelized with brown sugar and rum on a hot griddle; a simple yet elegant dessert served at Libreville restaurants. The exceptional sweetness of Gabonese pineapples makes this preparation particularly spectacular.', TRUE),
('cocktail_de_fruits_frais_fresh_fruit_cocktail_gabonese', 'Cocktail de Fruits Frais (Fresh Fruit Cocktail)', 68, 0.8, 17.2, 0.2, 1.8, 14.6, 200, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['cocktail de fruits frais (fresh fruit cocktail)', 'salade de fruits tropicaux', 'fruits frais melanges'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Mixed bowl of fresh tropical fruits including mango, papaya, pineapple, and banana; dressed with lime juice and coconut flakes. Served at restaurants and made at home as a light dessert showcasing Gabon''s extraordinary tropical fruit abundance.', TRUE),
('yaourt_a_la_mangue_maison_homemade_mango_yogurt_gabonese', 'Yaourt a la Mangue Maison (Homemade Mango Yogurt)', 98, 4.8, 16.4, 1.8, 0.4, 14.8, 200, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['yaourt a la mangue maison (homemade mango yogurt)', 'yaourt mangue', 'yogurt tropical mango'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Homemade yogurt mixed with fresh mango puree; made by artisan dairy producers in Libreville and sold at morning markets. A nutritious and refreshing dessert that reflects the small-scale dairy industry developing in urban Gabon.', TRUE),
('lait_caille_sucre_sweetened_curdled_milk_gabonese', 'Lait Caille Sucre (Sweetened Curdled Milk)', 84, 5.2, 10.4, 2.4, 0.0, 10.2, 200, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['lait caille sucre (sweetened curdled milk)', 'lait fermente sucre', 'lait caille vanille'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Fermented curdled milk sweetened with sugar and sometimes flavored with vanilla; a traditional dairy product sold in small plastic cups at markets. A probiotic-rich food with deep roots in Gabonese daily nutrition.', TRUE),
('biscuits_palmier_palmier_pastry_gabonese', 'Biscuits Palmier (Palmier Pastry)', 448, 6.4, 56.8, 22.4, 1.4, 18.8, 50, 15, 'research', ARRAY['biscuits palmier (palmier pastry)', 'elephant ears', 'oreilles d''elephant', 'palmier caramelise'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Caramelized puff pastry cookies in a palm-leaf shape; produced at artisan bakeries in Libreville. The palmier is a classic French pastry that has become a staple snack in Gabonese patisseries sold by the bag or box.', TRUE),
('tuile_aux_amandes_almond_tuile_gabonese', 'Tuile aux Amandes (Almond Tuile)', 482, 9.2, 54.6, 26.4, 2.8, 28.8, 30, 8, 'research', ARRAY['tuile aux amandes (almond tuile)', 'tuile croquante amande', 'cigarettes russe'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Ultra-thin crispy almond cookies curved like a roof tile; a classic French pastry produced at Libreville''s finest patisseries. Often served alongside ice cream or mousse at upscale Gabonese restaurants as a crunchy garnish.', TRUE),
('financier_chocolat_coco_chocolate_coconut_financier_gabonese', 'Financier Chocolat Coco (Chocolate Coconut Financier)', 448, 8.6, 46.4, 26.4, 3.8, 32.8, 50, 30, 'research', ARRAY['financier chocolat coco (chocolate coconut financier)', 'financier coco chocolat', 'mini cake choco coco'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Moist rectangular almond cake made with coconut and dark chocolate; an artisan pastry sold at Libreville''s premium bakeries. The combination of French financier technique with tropical ingredients is a hallmark of modern Gabonese patisserie.', TRUE),
('canele_de_libreville_libreville_canele_gabonese', 'Canele de Libreville (Libreville Canele)', 354, 5.8, 58.6, 9.8, 0.4, 32.4, 50, 30, 'research', ARRAY['canele de libreville (libreville canele)', 'canele bordelais', 'petit gateau vanille rhum'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Bordeaux-origin rum and vanilla pastry with a caramelized crust; made at specialist patisseries in Libreville. The canele''s French Bordeaux heritage makes it a specialty of Gabon''s most refined patisseries catering to the French expatriate community.', TRUE),
('opera_cake_gabonais_gabonese_opera_cake_gabonese', 'Opera Cake Gabonais (Gabonese Opera Cake)', 402, 6.8, 44.8, 22.4, 1.8, 32.6, 100, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['opera cake gabonais (gabonese opera cake)', 'opera au cafe', 'gateau opera'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Multi-layer French opera cake with coffee buttercream and chocolate ganache; a prestige dessert at Libreville''s finest patisseries. This technically demanding French confection demonstrates the high level of French pastry craft practiced in Gabon.', TRUE),
('millefeuille_tropical_tropical_millefeuille_gabonese', 'Millefeuille Tropical (Tropical Millefeuille)', 428, 6.2, 48.6, 23.8, 1.2, 26.4, 120, 120, 'research', ARRAY['millefeuille tropical (tropical millefeuille)', 'mille feuilles tropique', 'napoleon tropical'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Layered puff pastry with tropical fruit custard cream; a French pastry classic adapted with Gabonese tropical fruit at Libreville patisseries. The mille-feuille is considered one of the pinnacles of French pastry craft and is taken seriously by Gabonese pastry chefs.', TRUE),
('gateau_moelleux_coco_soft_coconut_cake_gabonese', 'Gateau Moelleux Coco (Soft Coconut Cake)', 362, 5.8, 46.4, 18.6, 2.4, 28.8, 100, 80, 'research', ARRAY['gateau moelleux coco (soft coconut cake)', 'gateau coco moelleux', 'cake humide coco'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Extremely soft and moist coconut cake made with coconut cream and desiccated coconut; a popular celebration cake at Gabonese parties and sold by the slice at bakeries. The intense coconut flavor and moist texture make it a beloved everyday indulgence.', TRUE),
('baba_au_rhum_tropical_tropical_rum_baba_gabonese', 'Baba au Rhum Tropical (Tropical Rum Baba)', 286, 5.4, 48.4, 6.8, 0.6, 26.8, 100, 80, 'research', ARRAY['baba au rhum tropical (tropical rum baba)', 'baba rhum fruits tropicaux', 'savarin tropical'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Yeast-raised cake soaked in rum syrup served with tropical fruit compote; a French classic found at Libreville restaurants. The rum baba with tropical fruit reflects French Antillean influence on Gabonese French culinary heritage.', TRUE),
('eclair_passion_fruit_passion_fruit_eclair_gabonese', 'Eclair Passion Fruit (Passion Fruit Eclair)', 308, 6.4, 38.4, 13.8, 0.8, 20.4, 80, 80, 'research', ARRAY['eclair passion fruit (passion fruit eclair)', 'eclair fruit de la passion', 'eclair tropical'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Choux pastry filled with passion fruit cream and topped with passion fruit glaze; a tropical twist on the classic French eclair at Libreville patisseries. The intensely aromatic passion fruit transforms this French pastry classic into something uniquely Gabonese.', TRUE),
('religieuse_au_cafe_coffee_cream_puff_tower_gabonese', 'Religieuse au Cafe (Coffee Cream Puff Tower)', 318, 6.8, 34.6, 16.8, 0.6, 18.4, 100, 100, 'research', ARRAY['religieuse au cafe (coffee cream puff tower)', 'religieuse cafe', 'chouquettes cafe'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Double choux puff pastry filled with coffee cream and decorated with fondant; a classic French pastry found at Libreville''s top patisseries. Gabonese coffee culture and French pastry tradition combine in this elegant presentation.', TRUE),
('paris_brest_tropical_tropical_paris_brest_gabonese', 'Paris Brest Tropical (Tropical Paris Brest)', 398, 7.8, 36.4, 25.8, 2.8, 18.6, 120, 120, 'research', ARRAY['paris brest tropical (tropical paris brest)', 'paris brest cajou', 'couronne choux cajou'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Ring-shaped choux pastry filled with praline cream adapted with local cashew praline; a prestigious pastry found at Libreville''s finest patisseries. The cashew praline substitution for traditional hazelnut gives this French classic a distinctly Gabonese character.', TRUE),
('profiteroles_au_chocolat_chocolate_profiteroles_gabonese', 'Profiteroles au Chocolat (Chocolate Profiteroles)', 312, 6.2, 28.6, 19.4, 0.8, 14.8, 100, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['profiteroles au chocolat (chocolate profiteroles)', 'choux glace chocolat', 'petits choux chocolat'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Small choux puffs filled with vanilla ice cream and drizzled with warm dark chocolate sauce; served at Libreville restaurants as a classic French dessert. Made with Sao Tomean dark chocolate, this dessert showcases the Gulf of Guinea''s cacao.', TRUE),
('gateau_au_yaourt_yogurt_cake_gabonese', 'Gateau au Yaourt (Yogurt Cake)', 308, 5.8, 46.4, 11.4, 0.6, 24.8, 100, 80, 'research', ARRAY['gateau au yaourt (yogurt cake)', 'gateau nature yaourt', 'cake yaourt simple'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Simple moist yogurt cake made with plain yogurt as the base measurement; the most popular homemade cake recipe in French-influenced Gabonese households. Easy to make with basic pantry ingredients, it is the quintessential everyday French-Gabonese family cake.', TRUE),
('gateau_renverse_a_la_papaye_papaya_upside_down_cake_gabonese', 'Gateau Renverse a la Papaye (Papaya Upside-Down Cake)', 258, 3.8, 44.6, 7.8, 1.2, 28.4, 100, 80, 'research', ARRAY['gateau renverse a la papaye (papaya upside-down cake)', 'tatin papaye', 'renverse papaye'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Caramelized papaya slices baked under a butter cake and inverted; a Gabonese dessert showcasing the country''s abundant papaya crop. The caramelized papaya gives a rich tropical flavor that pairs beautifully with vanilla butter cake.', TRUE),
('gateau_renverse_a_la_banane_plantain_plantain_upside_down_cake_gabonese', 'Gateau Renverse a la Banane Plantain (Plantain Upside-Down Cake)', 278, 4.2, 48.6, 8.4, 2.2, 24.8, 100, 80, 'research', ARRAY['gateau renverse a la banane plantain (plantain upside-down cake)', 'tatin plantain', 'renverse banane plantain'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Caramelized ripe plantain baked under a vanilla sponge and inverted; a Gabonese adaptation of the classic tarte tatin using plantain instead of apple. The deep caramelization of plantain creates complex sweet flavors.', TRUE),
('cake_marbre_cafe_coco_coffee_coconut_marble_cake_gabonese', 'Cake Marbré Café Coco (Coffee Coconut Marble Cake)', 368, 5.8, 46.4, 18.4, 1.8, 24.8, 100, 80, 'research', ARRAY['cake marbré café coco (coffee coconut marble cake)', 'marbré café coco', 'cake marbre bicolore'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Marble cake with swirls of coffee and coconut batter; a Gabonese bakery specialty combining two of the country''s beloved flavors. Sold by the slice at bakeries and whole at special events, this cake represents modern Gabonese patisserie creativity.', TRUE),
('pain_perdu_a_la_noix_de_coco_coconut_french_toast_gabonese', 'Pain Perdu a la Noix de Coco (Coconut French Toast)', 268, 8.4, 36.4, 10.4, 1.6, 12.8, 150, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['pain perdu a la noix de coco (coconut french toast)', 'french toast coco', 'tartine perdue coco'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Day-old baguette dipped in coconut milk and egg batter, fried until golden; a popular breakfast and street food in Libreville. The French toast tradition has been adopted in Gabon and the coconut milk substitution gives it a tropical character.', TRUE),
('pancakes_a_la_banane_banana_pancakes_gabonese', 'Pancakes a la Banane (Banana Pancakes)', 224, 6.2, 38.4, 5.8, 1.8, 14.6, 150, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['pancakes a la banane (banana pancakes)', 'pancakes banane', 'crepes epaisses banane'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Thick American-style pancakes flavored with mashed banana; sold at brunch spots and cafes in Libreville catering to the international community. The banana pancake has become popular among young urban Gabonese professionals.', TRUE),
('flan_aux_fruits_de_la_passion_passion_fruit_flan_gabonese', 'Flan aux Fruits de la Passion (Passion Fruit Flan)', 168, 5.8, 24.6, 5.2, 0.8, 20.4, 120, 120, 'research', ARRAY['flan aux fruits de la passion (passion fruit flan)', 'flan passion', 'flanc fruit de la passion'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Baked egg custard flan topped with fresh passion fruit coulis; a popular dessert at Gabonese restaurants. The intense floral acidity of passion fruit cuts through the richness of the egg custard creating a perfect balance of flavors.', TRUE),
('meringues_tropicales_tropical_meringues_gabonese', 'Meringues Tropicales (Tropical Meringues)', 318, 3.6, 79.8, 0.1, 0.0, 76.4, 30, 15, 'research', ARRAY['meringues tropicales (tropical meringues)', 'meringues passion', 'meringues mangue poudre'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Crispy baked meringues flavored with passion fruit or mango powder; produced at Libreville patisseries as petit-four confections. The light airy texture and tropical flavor make these meringues a signature of modern Gabonese pastry chefs.', TRUE),
('chocolats_artisanaux_gabon_gabonese_artisan_chocolates_gabonese', 'Chocolats Artisanaux Gabon (Gabonese Artisan Chocolates)', 548, 5.8, 52.6, 34.8, 4.4, 44.8, 30, 8, 'research', ARRAY['chocolats artisanaux gabon (gabonese artisan chocolates)', 'bonbons chocolat artisanal', 'pralines chocolat sao tome'], 'candy', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Hand-crafted chocolate bonbons made with cacao from Sao Tome and Principe using fruits and spices from Gabon; produced by a new generation of Gabonese chocolatiers. These premium chocolates represent the emerging luxury food craft sector in Libreville.', TRUE),
('barre_energetique_arachide_miel_peanut_honey_energy_bar_gabonese', 'Barre Energetique Arachide Miel (Peanut Honey Energy Bar)', 486, 14.8, 52.6, 24.4, 4.8, 28.4, 50, 50, 'research', ARRAY['barre energetique arachide miel (peanut honey energy bar)', 'barre proteines arachide', 'energy bar gabon'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Compressed bar of peanuts, oats, and forest honey; produced by small Gabonese food enterprises as a nutritious energy snack for outdoor workers and athletes. The use of Gabonese forest honey gives these bars a distinctive terroir-driven flavor.', TRUE),
('sables_afrique_african_inspired_shortbreads_gabonese', 'Sablés Afrique (African-Inspired Shortbreads)', 494, 5.8, 60.4, 26.2, 1.8, 22.6, 40, 12, 'research', ARRAY['sablés afrique (african-inspired shortbreads)', 'biscuits africains epices', 'sables palme gingembre'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Spiced shortbread cookies made with palm sugar, ginger, and cinnamon; a Gabonese artisan biscuit inspired by traditional spice combinations. Sold at craft food markets and through export to the Gabonese diaspora in France.', TRUE),
('beignets_digname_sucres_sweet_yam_fritters_gabonese', 'Beignets d''Igname Sucres (Sweet Yam Fritters)', 218, 2.6, 40.4, 5.2, 3.4, 8.6, 100, 40, 'research', ARRAY['beignets d''igname sucres (sweet yam fritters)', 'galettes igname sucrees', 'beignets yam doux'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Mashed yam fritters sweetened with sugar and fried until golden; sold at morning markets in northern Gabon where yam is the dominant starch. A popular breakfast street food among the Fang and Beti ethnic communities.', TRUE),
('lait_de_soja_sucre_sweet_soy_milk_gabonese', 'Lait de Soja Sucre (Sweet Soy Milk)', 54, 3.4, 6.2, 1.8, 0.2, 5.4, 250, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['lait de soja sucre (sweet soy milk)', 'lait soja', 'soya lait sucre'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Sweetened soy milk sold in plastic bags at morning markets; introduced by Chinese food entrepreneurs and now widely consumed in Libreville as an affordable breakfast drink and dairy alternative.', TRUE),
('beignets_de_patate_douce_sweet_potato_fritters_gabonese', 'Beignets de Patate Douce (Sweet Potato Fritters)', 206, 2.4, 36.8, 6.4, 2.8, 10.2, 100, 35, 'research', ARRAY['beignets de patate douce (sweet potato fritters)', 'galettes patate douce', 'fritters patate orange'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Mashed sweet potato mixed into a batter and deep-fried; naturally sweet and filling fritters sold at markets and roadside stalls throughout Gabon. The orange flesh gives a vivid color and natural sweetness.', TRUE),
('croquets_arachide_peanut_crunchy_cookies_gabonese', 'Croquets Arachide (Peanut Crunchy Cookies)', 512, 14.6, 52.4, 28.8, 4.2, 18.6, 40, 12, 'research', ARRAY['croquets arachide (peanut crunchy cookies)', 'biscuits cacahuete', 'cookies arachide croustillant'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Crunchy flat cookies made with ground peanuts, flour, and palm sugar; a traditional Gabonese homemade biscuit given to children as an after-school snack. Peanut cookies have deep roots in Central African domestic cooking.', TRUE),
('gateau_igname_yam_cake_gabonese', 'Gateau Igname (Yam Cake)', 236, 3.2, 44.8, 5.6, 3.2, 18.4, 100, 80, 'research', ARRAY['gateau igname (yam cake)', 'cake igname', 'gateau yam coco'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Moist cake made from pureed boiled yam mixed with coconut milk, sugar, and eggs; a traditional village dessert from northern and eastern Gabon. Yam cake is prepared for family gatherings and ceremonies among the Fang people.', TRUE),
('confiture_de_goyave_guava_jam_gabonese', 'Confiture de Goyave (Guava Jam)', 248, 0.6, 64.2, 0.2, 2.8, 56.8, 30, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['confiture de goyave (guava jam)', 'gelee de goyave', 'marmelade goyave'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Thick guava fruit jam made by slow-cooking guava pulp with sugar; spread on bread or baguette for breakfast throughout Gabon. Guava jam is one of the most common homemade preserves in Gabonese households given the abundance of wild guava.', TRUE),
('sirop_de_gingembre_ginger_syrup_drink_gabonese', 'Sirop de Gingembre (Ginger Syrup Drink)', 78, 0.2, 19.6, 0.0, 0.1, 18.8, 250, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['sirop de gingembre (ginger syrup drink)', 'eau de gingembre', 'ginger drink sucre'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Concentrated ginger syrup diluted with water and served cold; a street drink sold at markets throughout Gabon. The sharp warming bite of ginger is beloved in Gabonese food culture and this drink is consumed for both pleasure and health.', TRUE),
('limonade_bissap_gingembre_hibiscus_ginger_lemonade_gabonese', 'Limonade Bissap Gingembre (Hibiscus Ginger Lemonade)', 56, 0.2, 14.2, 0.0, 0.2, 13.4, 250, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['limonade bissap gingembre (hibiscus ginger lemonade)', 'bissap gingembre citron', 'cocktail hibiscus gingembre'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Combined hibiscus and ginger drink with lemon and sugar; sold at cultural events and food markets in Libreville. The combination of bissap''s tartness with ginger''s heat makes this a refreshing and stimulating tropical drink.', TRUE),
('beignets_de_courge_pumpkin_fritters_gabonese', 'Beignets de Courge (Pumpkin Fritters)', 188, 3.2, 28.6, 7.4, 2.4, 6.8, 100, 35, 'research', ARRAY['beignets de courge (pumpkin fritters)', 'galettes de potiron', 'fritters courge'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Seasoned pumpkin fritters deep-fried until golden; sold at morning markets in rural Gabon where squash and pumpkin are widely cultivated. A practical and nutritious street food using a vegetable grown throughout Gabon''s interior provinces.', TRUE),
('compote_de_banane_banana_compote_gabonese', 'Compote de Banane (Banana Compote)', 128, 0.8, 32.4, 0.2, 2.2, 24.6, 150, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['compote de banane (banana compote)', 'bananes cuites au sucre', 'banane caramelisee douce'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Slow-cooked banana compote with cinnamon and vanilla; served warm over rice porridge or as a standalone dessert. A simple and comforting dessert made year-round in Gabonese households using overripe bananas.', TRUE),
('gateau_de_riz_rice_cake_gabonese', 'Gateau de Riz (Rice Cake)', 218, 4.2, 42.8, 3.6, 0.6, 14.8, 100, 80, 'research', ARRAY['gateau de riz (rice cake)', 'cake de riz coco', 'pain de riz sucre'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Baked rice cake made with cooked rice, coconut milk, eggs, and sugar; a dense satisfying dessert sold at Gabonese markets on weekends. The combination of rice and coconut milk is a recurring flavor pairing in Gabonese sweet cooking.', TRUE),
('confiture_dananas_pimentee_spicy_pineapple_jam_gabonese', 'Confiture d''Ananas Pimentee (Spicy Pineapple Jam)', 238, 0.4, 60.8, 0.2, 1.4, 54.6, 30, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['confiture d''ananas pimentee (spicy pineapple jam)', 'marmelade ananas piment', 'jam ananas pili'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Pineapple jam made with a pinch of pili-pili for a sweet-hot contrast; a uniquely Gabonese condiment used on bread or as a glaze for grilled meats. The sweet-spicy combination reflects Gabon''s love of layered flavors.', TRUE),
('sucre_de_palme_palm_sugar_block_gabonese', 'Sucre de Palme (Palm Sugar Block)', 382, 0.4, 98.4, 0.1, 0.0, 92.8, 20, 20, 'research', ARRAY['sucre de palme (palm sugar block)', 'sucre de palme non raffine', 'jaggery palmier'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Solid blocks of unrefined palm sugar tapped from the sap of palm trees; sold at markets and used as a natural sweetener in Gabonese cooking and confectionery. Palm sugar has a distinctive caramel-molasses flavor distinct from cane sugar.', TRUE),
('biscuits_de_mais_souffles_puffed_corn_biscuits_gabonese', 'Biscuits de Mais Souffles (Puffed Corn Biscuits)', 388, 7.2, 78.4, 4.8, 4.6, 6.2, 40, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['biscuits de mais souffles (puffed corn biscuits)', 'souffles de maïs', 'chips maïs soufflees'], 'snack', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Light puffed corn snacks similar to corn puffs; produced by small food enterprises and sold at kiosks across Gabon. An affordable and light snack popular with all ages, particularly schoolchildren buying from tuck shops.', TRUE),
('tartine_de_confiture_maison_homemade_jam_toast_gabonese', 'Tartine de Confiture Maison (Homemade Jam Toast)', 246, 5.8, 44.8, 4.6, 1.8, 18.4, 100, NULL, 'research', ARRAY['tartine de confiture maison (homemade jam toast)', 'pain confiture tropicale', 'toast confiture maison'], 'street_food', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Baguette spread with homemade tropical fruit jam such as mango, pineapple or papaya; a common Gabonese breakfast sold at small canteens and roadside stalls. The tradition of jam-making from tropical fruits is widespread in Gabonese households.', TRUE),
('gateau_fondant_a_lavocat_avocado_fudge_cake_gabonese', 'Gateau Fondant a l''Avocat (Avocado Fudge Cake)', 328, 5.2, 36.4, 19.8, 4.8, 22.6, 100, 80, 'research', ARRAY['gateau fondant a l''avocat (avocado fudge cake)', 'cake avocat chocolat', 'fondant avocat'], 'dessert', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Dense chocolate-avocado cake using avocado as a butter substitute; a modern health-conscious dessert made at creative bakeries in Libreville. The rich fat content of Gabonese avocados makes them an ideal dairy-free baking ingredient.', TRUE),
('rouleaux_de_printemps_frits_gabonais_gabonese_fried_spring_rolls_gabonese', 'Rouleaux de Printemps Frits Gabonais (Gabonese Fried Spring Rolls)', 228, 7.8, 24.6, 11.2, 1.8, 2.4, 80, 30, 'research', ARRAY['rouleaux de printemps frits gabonais (gabonese fried spring rolls)', 'nems porc legumes', 'rouleaux frits mixtes'], 'appetizer', NULL, 1, 'GA', 'Crispy fried spring rolls filled with a mixture of vegetables, glass noodles, and minced pork; reflecting the Vietnamese community''s influence on Gabonese cuisine. Sold at Vietnamese-owned restaurants and at evening market food stalls.', TRUE),
